Commentary: Kagiso Rabada goes over the wicket, serves a fullish delivery, outside off, hint of away movement there. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
This one swings in, full and around middle and leg, at 140 clicks. Alex Lees tucks it towards square leg for a single. England and Alex Lees are up and running!
Leg bye! Swinging in, around the leg pole, on a length. Zak Crawley looks to flick this one but he misses. The ball goes towards square leg off his pads and the batters steal a leg bye.
Oh, good ball! Slightly shorter, nipping back in, around middle and leg. Alex Lees misses his tuck and gets hit high on his thigh pad.

A stifled appeal for LBW, turned down by the umpire. Another in-swinger, length ball, around the leg pole. Alex Lees looks to flick this but he misses and gets rapped on his pads. That was sliding down leg.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees lets that go through to the keeper.
Lungi Ngidi begins with a length ball from over the wicket, outside off, shaping away. Zak Crawley offers no shot.
Another length delivery, swinging away, in the channel outside off. Zak Crawley shoulders his arms at it.
Sticks to his good length, outside off, shaping away, at 132 clicks. Zak Crawley is happy to let that go.
Another out-swinger, outside off and on a length. Zak Crawley does not fiddle with that one.
Wide of off this time, swinging it away, on a good length. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Much fuller this time, outside off, at 133 clicks, shaping away. Zak Crawley is not tempted with that one. He lets it go. A maiden for Lungi Ngidi!

EDGED AND FOUR! A fuller one, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees leans to drive this one away from his body. But the ball goes off the outside edge and flies over Aiden Markram at second slip, towards third man for a boundary. A tough chance for him, but England have their first boundary.
Wide of off, swinging it away, on a length. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Shorter ball, outside off and swinging it away. Alex Lees shoulders his arms at it.
Oh, well bowled! A short ball, around middle and leg. Alex Lees sways away from it at the end.
Another stifled appeal there for LBW, but the umpire says no! An in-swinger now, around the leg pole, on a good length. Alex Lees misses his flick and gets rapped on his pads.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! South Africa have got an early breakthrough! Alex Lees escaped earlier in the over but not this time. Kagiso Rabada has his man! A shorter one, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees stays in his crease and looks to push this away, but the ball goes off the outside edge towards the keeper. Kyle Verreynne makes no mistake there.
Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Angling in, fuller in length, around off. Zak Crawley blocks it out
Fuller one again, around middle and off. Zak Crawley pushes it towards mid on and takes a single. He gets off the mark with that.
Pitches it up again, shaping this one away, around off. Ollie Pope lunges forward and blocks it out towards point.
An appeal for LBW, but turned down again and rightly so. This was sliding down leg. A length ball, swing in, around the leg pole. Ollie Pope misses his tuck and gets pinged on his pads.
Tad fuller, outside off, at 134 clicks. Ollie Pope leans forward and blocks it out with the outer half of his bat towards point.
Back of a length, outside off. Ollie Pope steps down the track and dabs it towards mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, swinging it down leg. Ollie Pope lets that one go. Kyle Verreynne does well diving to his left to stop the ball.
Edged and just short! Outside off, on a length. Ollie Pope looks to leave this one but the ball goes off his toe-end and lands just short of Aiden Markram at second slip.
Good-length, sliding down leg. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
Outside off, a length delivery, shaping away. Ollie Pope shoulders his arms at it.
Much fuller now, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it off the front foot towards the fielder at mid off.
In the channel outside the off pole, length delivery. Ollie Pope does not fiddle with that one.
A good-length delivery, swinging away, outside off. Zak Crawley lets that go through to the keeper.

FOUR! Lovely shot! First confident shot from Zak Crawley and England! Fuller one, around middle. Zak Crawley presents the full face of the bat and drives it down the ground away from mid on and towards the boundary for four.

Angling in, on a length, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley blocks it towards short leg. The fielder there collects the ball on a bounce and throws it back at the stumps without looking. Zak Crawley was well in though.
Good-length delivery, outside off, swinging away. Zak Crawley is happy to let that go.
Beaten! Lovely ball! On a good length, around the fourth stump line. Zak Crawley looks to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Lungi Ngidi serves it on a length, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Beaten! In the channel outside off, a good-length delivery. Ollie Pope gets beaten on his outside edge while trying to block this one.
Fuller one, around middle and off. Ollie Pope blocks it out from within his crease.
Angling in, fuller length, darting it on the pads. Ollie Pope flicks it through the mid-wicket. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters grab three runs.
A length delivery, outside off. Zak Crawley shoulders his arms at it.
Oh, close! Another length delivery, outside off. Zak Crawley looks to defend this one but he bails out in the end.
Beaten again! Kagiso Rabada is searching for that outside edge. On a length, around the fourth stump line. Zak Crawley looks to block this but get gets beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge.
A fuller one, shaping away, wide of off. Ollie Pope is happy to let that go.
Pulls his length back a tad, outside off, on a length. Ollie Pope lifts his bat to leave this one but the ball goes off his toe-end and rolls away towards second slip.
A length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope blocks this one watchfully.
Well bowled! A few outswingers earlier, and this time Lungi Ngidi nips this one back in, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope looks to flick this one but he misses and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ollie Pope walks across and steps out to flick this one through mid-wicket. Three taken!
Outside off, on a good length. Zak Crawley looks to block this one but he misses. Well away from his blade though.
Another three! Back of a length, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope pulls this one in the gap between mid-wicket and mid on. Three taken.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Edged and safe! Slightly short, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley looks to flick this but he gets a leading edge and that falls way short of Kagiso Rabada.

FOUR! Leading edge again but this time it runs away for a boundary! A length ball, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley looks to tuck this towards square leg, but the ball goes off his leading edge away from the fielder at gully for a boundary.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! This time it's a wicket! Well, this was certainly bound to happen sooner rather than later. Kagiso Rabada gets another wicket and England are now two down. On a length, outside off, not much movement there. Zak Crawley leans to block this one but the ball goes off his outside edge towards second slip. Aiden Markram dives to his left and takes a good low catch.
Howout: c Aiden Markram b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: A length ball, down the leg side. Joe Root looks to flick this one but he misses.

A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire says no! Dean Elgar opts for a review. A length ball, swinging in, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope misses his flick and gets hit on his pads. No bat involved there. Ball Tracking indicates that it was missing wickets. The on-field decision stands and South Africa lose a review.
Oh, lovely ball! Tight leave from Ollie Pope! A length ball, nipping back in sharply, around the fourth stump line. Ollie Pope shoulders his arms at it.
Much fuller now, outside off. Ollie Pope pushes it off the front foot towards mid off.
On a good length, around middle and off. Ollie Pope shuffles across and tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Lungi Ngidi fires this one on the pads, a length ball. Joe Root flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.

Leg bye! Another length ball, tailing back in, around his thigh pad. Joe Root looks to clip this one away but he misses. The ball deflects off his thigh pad and goes towards fine leg. A leg bye taken!
Rabada is on target again! Lands a fullish delivery, around off. It is not that full to drive and Root defends it off the outside half of his blade towards point.
Bangs it short, on middle. Root picks the length quickly and pulls it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Oh, what a delivery! Absolute ripper! Rabada lands it short of good length and the ball just takes off sharply after pitching. It is on off. Root hops and manages to defend it towards the off side.
Lands on a length, on off. Root blocks it out this time.
Ohh, another nasty short delivery! Angling into the body and Root manages to defend it onto the turf as he takes his one hand off the handle.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Starts off with a full delivery. It shapes back in from the off stump line. Pope works it to mid-wicket.
Bowls a short delivery but it is way down the leg side. Pope lets it go.
Goes fuller and it swings in again. However, it drifts down the leg side as Pope misses his flick shot.
Tad shorter and around leg. Pope looks to clip it away but misses. The ball hits him around his chest and rolls towards the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Lands on a good length and it is outside off. Root pushes at it tentatively and gets beaten.
Goes fuller and it is down the leg side again. Root looks to flick it but misses as the keeper collects it with a dive.
Starts off with a tad shorter length and it is outside off as well. Pope rides the bounce and punches it through cover-point. The batters run three.
Back of a length and outside off. Root leaves it alone.
This is an in-swinger! It lands on a length, around off and shapes back in. Root defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Quality shot from a quality batter! Nortje bowls it short and wide outside off. Root is quick to gauge that length and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
Serves it on a good length and it is around off. It shapes back in but Root is aware off his off stump and leaves it comfortably.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Root pushes it towards backward point.
Jansen has not got his line right so far! He bowls it full and way down the leg side again. Pope lets it go.
An appeal for LBW but turned down! Good late in-swing there. The ball lands on a length, on off and shapes back in. Pope looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads but it is going down leg.
On a length, on middle. Pope defends it towards the leg side.
Nicely driven! This is a fullish delivery, on off. Pope leans forward and drives it through covers. The batters run three as the fielder cuts it off.

OUT! LBW! Marco Jansen gets a big fish here! Joe Root departs and England lose their third wicket. Jansen bowls it on a fullish length, on middle. It shapes back in nicely and Root looks to flick it away. He misses and the ball hits his pads. There is a big appeal and the umpire raises his finger. However, Root decides to take the DRS, The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracking indicates that it is just clipping the leg pole. It is the umpire's call on wickets hitting. So the original decision stays! Joe Root has to walk back.
Howout: lbw b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Lands on a length, around off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it towards the off side.
FOUR! Lovely drive by Pope! Anrich Nortje bowls a half-volley, outside off. Pope leans forward and creams it through cover-point for a boundary.
FOUR! Anrich Nortje overcompensates and Pope gets it away for another boundary. Short and wide outside off. Pope stands tall and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
Lands it just short of good length, on middle. Pope looks to nudge it away but misses. The ball hits him high on the pads.
Goes fuller on middle. Pope looks to flick it away but gets an inside edge onto his pads this time.
Pulls his length back, it is outside off and Pope guides it with the angled blade towards point.
Nortje angles it on the pads. Pope looks to clip it away. The ball brushes his pads and goes behind square towards the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Goes fuller on middle. Pope flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.

An appeal for a caught behind but Elgar decides to not take a review. This one lands on a length, on middle. It shapes in again and Pope looks to flick it but misses. The ball brushes his thigh pad and the keeper takes it behind the stumps moving to his left. No damage done in the end.
A fullish delivery, around off. Pope pushes it towards covers for a single.
Serves a length delivery, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Well played by Jonny. This is a fullish delivery that shapes into middle. Jonny Bairstow defends it off the middle of his blade.
Edged and safe! On a length, shaping away, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to block this one but he gets an outside edge that does not carry to the fielder at second slip.
This is a fullish delivery that swings back in again. Pope looks to flick it away but misses and the ball hits the pads.
Back of a length, on middle. Pope works it towards mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Anrich Nortje gets his radar right and gets a big wicket of Jonny Bairstow! South Africa are right on top now! Anrich Nortje bowls it full. The ball shapes in nicely into middle. Jonny Bairstow looks to drive but misses it completely and the ball shatters the stumps. Both Joe Root and Jonny Bairstow are back in the hut, they were the ones who were at the forefront of English charge earlier in the summer. South Africa showing their might with the ball again!
Howout: b Anrich Nortje

Commentary: Lands on a good length and it is outside off. Stokes leaves it alone.
Here we go...Stokes is down the track straightaway! Stokes charges down the track and makes some room as well. Nortje follows him and Stokes ends up blocking it in the end.
Back of a length, on off. Stokes blocks it from his crease this time.

Oh, that's an absolute beauty! Jansen lands on a good length and it is outside off. This time he gets a sharp seam movement into the batter. Pope leans forward to defend it but the ball beats the inside edge of his blade and goes through to the keeper.
A fullish delivery on middle. Hint of shape into the batter again. Pope clips it to mid-wicket.
This is lovely bowling. He has found his line now and is making some good use of the swing he is getting. It is fuller on off, shapes in and Pope drives it off the inside half of his blade.
This time an inside edge comes to the rescue of the batter! A full delivery that shapes into middle. Pope looks to push it away but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Full delivery on middle and off again. Pope works it wide of mid on for a single.
Jansen continues to bowl full, it is on middle and Stokes blocks it out.
Fuller delivery and around off. Pope pushes it off the front foot to mid off.
Lands on a length, on middle. Pope defends it towards the leg side as he takes his one hand off the blade.
FOUR! Nortje tries something differet and pays the price. Short and wide outside off. Pope jumps and upper-cuts it towards the backward point fence for a boundary.
Angles it into the body. Tad shorter in length as well and Pope works it to fine leg for a single.
Bowls a fullish delivery, outside off. Stokes drives it firmly to covers. However, Elgar does well to half-stop it and a single is taken.
A fullish delivery that shapes into middle and leg. Pope flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.

Beaten! This is something we have seen from Stokes all throughout this summer. Jansen bowls it just short of good length, on middle. Stokes dances down the track and looks to heave it towards the leg side but misses.
Back of a length, on leg. Stokes tries to clip it away. However, the ball brushes his thigh pad and goes towards fine leg. Two leg byes taken.
Lands on a length, on off. Stokes dabs it towards cover-point for a single.
On a length, on off. Pope defends it towards cover.
A fullish delivery around off. Pope goes across and works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Pulls his length back a bit. However, he drifts down the leg side and Stokes misses it as he tries to clip it away.
A fuller ball, outside off. at around 140 clicks. Ollie Pope leans forward to drive this one but he gets undone by the pace.
Pitches it up again, swinging away, outside off. Ollie Pope presses forward and drives this one away from his body wide of mid off. Two taken.
Kagiso Rabada drops it short now, around middle. Ollie Pope goes for the pull shot but the ball goes off the inside edge onto his body and rolls towards square leg. A single taken.
A length ball now, around off, at 140 clicks. Ben Stokes blocks it out solidly.
Shaping away, wide of off, a fuller one. Ben Stokes shoulds his arms at it.
Tad fuller, around middle. Ben Stokes blocks it out watchfully.
Marco Jansen continues to swing the ball back into the right-hander, around middle on a length. Ollie Pope defends it out.
Angling in, on a length, around the thigh pad. Ollie Pope tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Glorious! An overpitched delivery, around middle. Ben Stokes shows the full face of the bat and drives it down the ground for a beautiful boundary.
Down the leg side, a length delivery. Ben Stokes looks to flick this one but he misses.
Outside off this time, shaping away, on a good length. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
FOUR! Another gorgeous shot from the England skipper! Marco Jansen overcooks this one, around off. Ben Stokes once again, drives it firmly down the ground for a boundary. Good over for England!
Tight leave! A length ball, tailing back in sharply, outside off. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
Wide of off this time, on a good length. Ollie Pope lets that go through to the keeper.
Kagiso Rabada drops it short this time, around middle and off. Ollie Pope is happy to let that go. Kyle Verreynne jumps and does well to collect the ball.
A good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope taps it towards point and takes a single.
This one lands on a length, and swings away, outside off. Ben Stokes gets beaten while trying to block this one.
A short ball this time, on the body. Ben Stokes pulls it towards square leg for a single.
Anrich Nortje comes 'round the wicket for the left-hander, serves a fuller ball, around middle and off. Ben Stokes defends it out.
On a length this time, around middle and off again. Ben Stokes defends it out watchfully.
Angling in this time, on a length, around the leg pole. Ben Stokes tucks it toward fine leg and rotates the strike.
Anrich Nortje goes over the wicket now, serves a length ball, nips it back in, outside off, at 141 clicks. Ollie Pope does not fiddle with it.
This one angles in, on a good length, on the pads. Ollie Pope flicks it through square leg for a brace.
Back of a length, around middle and off. Ollie Pope blocks it out off the back foot.
A fuller ball, wide of off, shaping away. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Another one wide of off, swinging away, fuller in length. Ben Stokes is not interested in playing that.
FOUR! Another fine stroke by Ben Stokes! This is full in length, around off. Ben Stokes drives it uppishly and away from the mid off for a boundary.
Swing and a miss! Shorter ball, width on offer. Ben Stokes stays in his crease and looks to slash this one away but he fails to get any bat on that.
Beaten! Back of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes stays in his crease and tries to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Kagiso Rabada sprays this one down the leg side, on a good length. Ben Stokes lets it go. Kyle Verreynne dives to his right and makes a good stop.

EDGED AND DROPPED! A chance goes down. Fuller one, wide of off. Ollie Pope looks to drive this away from his body and he manages to get an outside edge towards third slip. Keegan Petersen dives to his right, sticks his right hand out, but manages to get only his fingertips on the ball. Two taken.

FOUR! Ollie Pope brings up his fifty in style! A fuller one, outside off. Ollie Pope lunges forward and creams his drive through cover for a boundary. A lovely knock from him so far! He will want to convert this into a big one.
Leg bye! On a good length, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope misses his tuck and gets hit on his pads. The ball rolls away towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.
EDGED AND FOUR! Outside off, fuller one. Ben Stokes looks to drive this one but he gets a thick outside side over the second slip fielder for a boundary.
Shorter one, outside off, shaping away. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Anrich Nortje gets rid of the England skipper on the final delivery before Lunch! What a session this has been for the visitors. England are in deep trouble after having lost half their side now. Coming to the delivery - A shorter one from 'round the wicket, outside off. Ben Stokes stays in his crease and looks to push this one away but he gets an outside edge that flies towards third slip. Keegan Petersen, there takes a good catch. That will be Lunch on Day 1.
Howout: c Keegan Petersen b Anrich Nortje

Commentary: Quick single to begin proceedings in the second session! A shorter ball, outside off. Ollie Pope taps it towards point and scampers across to the other end.
Much fuller now, outside off. Ben Foakes blocks it out with the toe-end of his bat.
Another full-length delivery, around middle and off. Ben Foakes defends it out.
This one nips back in off a short-length delivery, around middle. Ben Foakes looks to flick this one but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad.

Another in-swinger, around middle and leg, a length delivery. Ben Foakes tries to flick this one but he gets a sight inside edge back onto his pads. The ball rolls towards point and the batters cross ends. Ben Foakes is off the mark!
Fuller ball, outside off. Ollie Pope lunges forward and drives it firmly through cover-point. Two taken.
Anrich Nortje comes over the wicket, serves a full ball, outside off, swinging in, at 148 clicks. Ben Foakes leaves it alone.
Another speedy delivery! Outside off, a length ball, tailing back in, at 147 clicks. Ben Foakes dabs it towards point.
Good-length delivery, outside off, Ben Foakes blocks it out watchfully.
FOUR! Good timing on that one! A fuller ball, swinging in, around middle and leg, at 147 clicks. Ben Foakes flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. First boundary of the afternoon session.
Anrich Nortje serves it on a length, outside off. Ben Foakes blocks it out.
Down the leg side, slightly shorter this time. Ben Foakes looks to flick this one but he misses. A stifled appeal there for caught behind but the umpire is not interested in that one.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. Ollie Pope gets on his toes and dabs it towards backward point.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ollie Pope leans to drive but the ball goes off his inner half through mid-wicket for a brace.
Kagiso Rabada pitches this one up, around off. Ollie Pope pushes it back to the bowler.
Beaten! A beauty by Kagiso Rabada! On a length, outside off, shaping away. Ollie Pope looks to block this but he gets beaten on his outside edge.
A good-length ball, nipping back in, around off. Ollie Pope gets an inside edge onto his pads while trying to block this one.
Back of a lenngth, outside off. Ollie Pope stays back and cuts it through point for a brace.
Angling in, a length ball, darting it on the pads. Ben Foakes tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Width on offer now, a length ball, at 148 clicks. Ollie Pope looks to cut this away but he misses.
Much fuller this time, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it towards the fielder at mid off.
Anrich Nortje drops it short now, around middle. Ollie Pope miscues his pull shot through square leg for a single.
Back of a length, down the leg side. Ben Foakes looks to leave this one but the ball brushes off his thigh pad and goes towards short fine leg. No run taken there.
Another bouncer from Anrich Nortje. Ben Foakes ducks under it and lets it go.
Lands on a good length, around off. The ball seams away a bit and Pope defends it off the outside half of his blade towards cover-point.
Lands on a length, around off. Pope guides it towards the gully fielder.
Rabada bangs it short on middle. Pope pulls it to deep backward square leg. Ngidi loses his balance as he stops this ball and the batters take two.
A tad shorter again, outside off. Pope leaves it alone.
Rabada bowls this just short of good length, outside off. Pope decides to leave it alone again. Nice carry to the keeper.
Back of a length, on off. Pope defends it towards point and sends back his partner who was looking for a run.
Serves it on a length, around off. Foakes blocks it out solidly towards the off side.
Goes fuller on middle this time. Foakes works it right of the mid on fielder.
Pulls his length back, on middle. Foakes looks to work it towards the leg side but gets hit high on the pads and the ball rolls towards the off side.

OUT! BOWLED! Anrich Nortje strikes again and England lose their sixth wicket now! Anrich Nortje with a pacy length delivery, around off. Foakes looks to defend it from his crease but does so away from his body. The ball catches the inside edge of his blade and knocks over the stumps. England continue to lose wickets and with Anrich Nortje bowling over 90 mph regularly in these gloomy conditions, it is only going to get tougher for English batters from hereon.
Howout: b Anrich Nortje

Commentary: Lands on a length and outside off. Broad leaves it alone.

Here we go...bouncer to Broad now! It is quite well directed, angling into the body from 'round the wicket. Broad looks to duck under it but gets hit on his shoulders. The ball rolls towards the off side.
Kagiso Rabada begins with a length ball, swinging in, around off. Ollie Pope pushes it towards cover. He wanted a single there but is sent back by his partner.
Fuller now, around off. Ollie Pope drives it past mid off. Two taken. We are underway on Day 2!
FOUR! First boundary of the morning! Shorter ball now, down leg. Ollie Pope pulls it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Pitches it up now, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope lunges forward and drives it to the fielder at cover.
Another full ball, outside off, swinging away. Ollie Pope drives it away from his body to the fielder at mid off.

DROPPED! Oh, dear! A big chance for South Africa goes down! A length ball, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope leans to block this one but the ball goes off the outside edge towards first slip. Sarel Erwee there gets his hands to the ball, he juggles it two times, and eventually puts it down. Kagiso Rabada was already celebrating there, but he now stands in disbelief.
Anrich Nortje begins with a shorter one from 'round the wicket, outside off, swinging away. Stuart Broad leaves it alone.
Oh, well bowled! Another shorter one, outside off, swinging away. Stuart Broad gets beaten on the outside edge while trying to block this one.
Anrich Nortje drops it short again, outside off, at 146 clicks. Stuart Broad leaves it alone.
Swing and a miss! Anrich Nortje continues to trouble Broad with the short ball, the line is outside off again. Stuart Broad looks to push this one away but he misses.
Back of a length, outside off. Stuart Broad lets that go through to the keeper.
Another play and a miss! Shorter one, wide of off. Stuart Broad looks to cut this away but he misses.
Angling in, fuller one and around middle and leg. Ollie Pope flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Wide of off this time, fuller in length. Ollie Pope presses forward and drives this one away from his body and towards deep point. Only a single.
Swinging into the left-hander, full again, around off. Stuart Broad drives and finds the fielder at mid off.
Stuart Broad takes the aerial route now! Pitched-up delivery, outside off. Stuart Broad lifts this one over cover. Two taken.
Kagiso Rabada drops it short now, shaping it away, outside off. Stuart Broad stays in his crease and looks to push this away on the off side but he fails to get any bat on it.
Lovely ball! A yorker-length delivery, swinging down leg. Stuart Broad backs away and fails to dig this one out.
On a good length, nipping back in sharply, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope looks to flick this but he misses and gets rapped on high on his pads.
Another length delivery, angling in, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope works it away through mid-wicket. Lungi Ngidi chases the ball and keeps it down to two runs.
Swinging down leg, a length ball. Ollie Pope leaves it alone. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left and makes a good stop.
This one swings away, around off, on a length. Ollie Pope taps it towards cover-point.
Much fuller on this occasion, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it towards cover. Only a single.

FOUR! Edgy runs! Too short on this occasion, around off. Stuart Broad looks to pull this one but he manages to only get a slight top edge over the keeper. The ball runs away towards third man for a boundary.
A length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope defends it out.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Kagiso Rabada has his man! Sarel Erwee can breathe a sigh of relief. His drop catch did not prove to be costly. A fuller one, outside off, not much movement there. Ollie Pope strides forward and goes for the drive once again. This time the ball goes off the inside edge and back onto the stumps. South Africa have got their seventh wicket. Ollie Pope walks off to a round of applause. His fine knock comes to an end.
Howout: b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Fuller one, swinging away, around off. Matthew Potts drives it towards mid off.
Shorter one this time, around middle and off. Matthew Potts ducks under it and leaves it alone.
Oh, well bowled! On a length, shaping away, outside off. Matthew Potts stays in his crease and looks to block this but the gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, outside off. Matthew Potts covers the line of the ball and blocks it out.
FOUR! Nicely done! Shorter one, around off. Stuart Broad uses the depth of his crease, clears his front foot, and punches it through cover for a boundary.
Another back-of-a-length delivery, around middle. Stuart Broad once again pushes it off the back foot towards long on. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters pick up three runs.
Swing and a miss! Shorter one, outside off. Matthew Potts looks to slash this one away but he misses.
Swinging away, outside off, on a length. Matthew Potts dabs it towards point.
Back of a length, around off. Matthew Potts sways away from that one.
A fuller one, wide of off. Matthew Potts gets down on his knee and drives it over point. Two taken. Matthew Potts is off the mark!
Play and a miss! A length ball, swinging away, wide of off. Stuart Broad looks to drive it away but he fails to get any bat on that.
An in-swinger this time, a length ball, down leg. Stuart Broad backs away and looks to flicks this away but he misses and gets rapped high on his thigh pad.
Big swing and a miss from Stuart Broad! Tad shorter now, outside off. Stuart Broad makes room and looks to hoick this over mid-wicket but he fails to get any bat on it.
Good-length delivery, on the pads. Stuart Broad flicks it aerially towards mid-wicket. Two taken.

OUT! TAKEN! Kagiso Rabada gets his fourth wicket and South Africa have their eighth! Smart bowling from Kagiso Rabada! Very full ball on this occasion, wide of off. Stuart Broad makes room and stretches to reach the ball. He opens the face of the bat and ends up chipping it towards point. Dean Elgar there takes a good low catch.
Howout: c Dean Elgar b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Bye! A length ball, nipping back in. Jack Leach leaves it alone. A little fumble by Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps, allows the batters to steal in a bye.
Beaten! Tad shorter, outside off. Jack Leach looks to block this one but he misses.
Shortish ball, outside off again. Jack Leach dabs it towards point. He wanted a single there but is sent back by Matthew Potts. Good call from him.
Beaten again! Back of a length, outside off. Jack Leach stays in his crease and looks to push this away but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
This one nips back in, around middle and leg. Jack Leach misses his flick and gets hit high on his thigh pad.

FOUR! Streaky boundary! On a length, outside off. Jack Leach lunges forward to drive this one with an angled bat, but the ball goes off the outer half past the diving fielder at gully. It rolls away towards third man for a boundary.
Well bowled! Much fuller this time, outside off. Jack Leach leans to drive this one but he misses.
Serves a good length delivery and it is outside off. Pott defends it inside the line of the ball.
Angles it into middle and leg. Potts works it bit uppishly but in the gap through mid-wicket for a couple.
Serves a fullish delivery, outside off. Potts goes for a drive but does so without much foot movement and gets beaten.
Beats him again! Just short of good length and around off. The ball pitches and seams away a bit. Potts looks to defend it off the back foot but misses.
Almost an action replay of the last delivery, maybe tad fuller. It is on a good length and around off again. Seams away and beats the outside edge of Pott's blade as he looks to defend.
Goes for a wild swing this time but misses. Lands on a good length again and it is outside off. Potts swings across the line but misses.
FOUR! Slashes and slashes hard for a boundary! Short and outside off. Leach cuts and gets a thick outside edge as the ball runs away through the gully region for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Leach blocks it out.
Back of a length and outside off. Leach looks to guide it behind square on the off side but misses.
Swing and a miss! Short and wide outside off. Leach throws his bat at it but misses.
FOUR! Nicely played! Back of a length and around off. Leach rides the bounce and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Tad shorter again and around off. Leach plays inside the line of the ball.
Beaten all ends up! Rabada bowls it in that channel, outside off. Pott tries to work it towards the leg side but ball seams away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, around leg. Potts looks to clip it but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Fullish delivery and outside off. Potts leaves it alone.
On a good length and outside off. Potts goes for an ambitious drive but misses,
Another play and miss! A good length delivery and outside off. Potts tries to push it away but misses.
Back of a length, on off. Potts blocks it out this time.
Short and wide outside off. Leach looks to cut it but misses. Jansen needs to be closer to the off pole.
Overcompensates this time and bowls it full, on middle and leg. Leach clips it through mid-wicket. The batters run three.
A fullish delivery and it is swinging into middle. Potts blocks it off the front foot.
Fuller and around off. Potts leans forward and drives it to covers for a single.
Loses his radar against the left-hander again! Back of a length and it is down the leg side. Leach leaves it alone.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Marco Jansen finally gets his radar right and gets rid of Leach here. This is a fullish delivery, on off. Leach goes for an expansive drive without much foot movement. The ball swings into him a bit and knocks over the off pole. Nine wickets down now and South Africa would be looking to wrap this innings quickly now.
Howout: b Marco Jansen

Commentary: Lands on a good length and around off. The ball seams away a bit and beats the outside edge of Potts blade as he looks to defend.
This time an inside edge! Serves it on a good length again, around off. Potts looks to defend but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Serves a good length and outside off. Potts plays it inside the line of the ball.
On a length and outside off. Potts pushes at it away from his body again and gets beaten again.
A fullish delivery, around off. Potts looks to work it towards the leg side but gets the outside edge. The ball goes in the air and towards the vacant point region. A single taken.

OUT! LBW! Kagiso Rabada ends with a five-wicket haul! A much-needed reward for his hard work. He was brilliant with the ball on Day 1 and bowled his heart out on Day 2 as well and has now rightly got his name on Lord's honours board. Coming to the ball - It lands on a good length, on middle, and seams back in slightly. James Anderson looks to clip it away but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is a huge appeal. The umpire raises his finger and Rabada roars in delight! James Anderson though takes the DRS. However, there is no bat involved and the Ball Tracking also shows three reds. The original decision will stay and England are all-out for 165!
Howout: lbw b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: James Anderson with his typical outswinger! It lands on a good length and is outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
James Anderson goes tad shorter and comes closer to the off pole. Agan an outswinger and Elgar is happy to leave that alone.
Goes fuller and it is down the leg side. Elgar looks to clip it but misses. The ball brushes his pads and goes towards right of Foakes. He dives and makes a good stop.
Serves it on a good length, around off. Elgar knows that he is better off leaving these deliveries and he does exactly that.
Tad fuller, on off. Elgar defends it off the front foot towards covers and takes his first run of the game. South Africa are underway as well!
This one pitches around leg and swings further down the leg side. Sarel Erwee looks to flick it but misses and Foakes again with makes a good stop diving to his right.
Starts off from 'round the wicket and lands it on a length, on off. Elgar with a solid block off the front foot.
FOUR! Glorious shot! First boundary for Elgar and South Africa! Broad overpitches it, on middle. Elgar leans forward and drives it past mid on for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Elgar defends it off the outside half of his blade.
Nicely played! Broad goes fuller in search of some swing. It is on off and Elgar drives it nicely through covers. The fielder though cuts it off as Elgar comes back for the second run.
Pulls his length back a bit, on middle. Elgar blocks it out.

Serves it on a good length and around off. Elgar takes his one hand off the handle as he defends it. The ball goes off the outside half of his blade towards fourth slip and the fielder there dives to stop it. There was swing for James Anderson in his first over but not much for Broad in his first over.
Lands it on a length, on off. Sarel Erwee blocks it nicely off the front foot.

Jimmy has drifted down the leg side again. He did the same two times in his first over and got away with it and he has got away with this one as well. It is around leg and fuller. Sarel Erwee looks to flick it but misses. The ball brushes his pads and goes to the right of Foakes. He half-stops it and a leg bye is taken.
On a length, on middle. Elgar works it towards mid-wicket.
Serves it on a good length and it is outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Lands on a length again, on off. Elgar is solid in defence this time.
Goes tad shorter and it is outside off as well. Elgar is happy and pretty comfortable in his leave.

Inside edge there! Broad serves it on a good length, around off. The ball seams back in and Erwee gets the inside edge onto his pads as he looks to defend. A very optimistic appeal from Broad but no damage done.
FOUR! Sarel Erwee is off the mark with a boundary! Broad goes straighter and it is fuller as well. Erwee clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Lands on a good length and outside off. Erwee with a watchful leave.
Broad serves it on a good length, angling into off. Erwee defends it back to the bowler.

Goes tad fuller and it is angled into off from Broad. Erwee tries to drive but does not keep his bat straight and angles it towards the leg side. The ball goes off the outside half of his blade towards the off side.
On a length and around off. Erwee pushes it right of cover for a single.
This is fuller and down the leg side. Sarel Erwee looks to flick it but misses.
On a good length and outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Erwee defends it onto his pitch.
Goes a bit fuller on leg. Erwee clips it to mid-wicket.
A fullish delivery, around leg. Erwee tries to flick it away but misses and gets hit on his pads. The fielders appeal but Anderson knew that it was going down leg.
Anderson with a fuller delivery on leg again. Erwee clips it to fine leg for a couple.
On a length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Serves it on a good length and it around off. Elgar makes a watchful leave again.
Elgar has loads of patience in his game and is not going to go after this wide deliveries. This one again is on a good length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
On a length, on middle. Elgar works it to mid-wicket.
Better from Broad! Serves it on a good length but this time it is closer to the off pole. Elgar is in two minds whether to leave it or play. He ends up making a good leave in the end.
This time an easy leave. It is on a length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.

Ohh..almost a wicket there! On a good length, around off. Erwee is late on his leave and gets the inside edge of his blade. The ball goes just past the stumps and Foakes half-stops it with a dive to his right. A single taken.

An absolute ripper this time! Anderson continues to bowl it on a good length, closer to off and this time the ball swings and seams away. Elgar is beaten all ends up as he looks to defend it off the front foot.
On a length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Bowls it tad fuller and angling into middle and leg. Elgar looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal but the umpire says no..
Lands on a good length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Again it is too wide outside off. Elgar makes an easy leave.
Broad just like his new ball partner, bowls a good length delivery. It is outside off and Erwee leaves it alone.
This is too wide outside off again. On a length and too easy for Erwee as he leaves it.
Serves it on a good length and it is around off. Erwee leaves it alone as the ball seams away a bit.
Goes fuller on middle. Erwee works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
On a length, on off. Elgar blocks it off the front foot.

Elgar is given out caught behind but he has reviewed it straightaway. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracking also shows that the ball is missing the stumps and the decision will be overturned. This delivery lands on a good length, on off. It comes back in sharply and beats Elgar as he looks to defend. The ball brushes his pads on the way and Foakes takes the catch behind the stumps. The umpire raises his finger after an appeal but it is overturned in the end.
Lands on a good length and outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
A fullish delivery on middle. Erwee looks to drive but gets the inside half of his blade. The ball goes towards the backward square leg region for a single.
On a length, on middle. Elgar defends it towards mid-wicket.
Lands on a good length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
A fuller ball, swinging in, around the leg pole. Dean Elgar misses his flick and gets rapped on his pad.
Tad shorter and outside off again. Elgar with an easy leave again.
A fuller delivery on middle. Erwee pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length and down the leg side. Erwee leaves it alone.

Potts goes fuller and he bowls it around off this time. Erwee shows the full face of his blade and drives it past mid off. The ball though is cut off by the fielder before reaching the ropes and the batters run three.

FOUR! Potts finds the edge this time but Crawley is late to react at second slip and the ball goes away for a boundary in the end. Back of a length and around off. Bit of swing away from the batter. Elgar tries to punch it away. However, he gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes quite quickly towards Zak Crawley. It is just over him and the English opener gets his hands to the ball but fails to grab it and Elgar gets away with a lucky boundary.
On a length and angling into leg. Elgar clips it to fine leg for a single.
Lovely delivery! Potts bowls a fullish delivery. It is around off and Erwee tries to drive it away. However, the ball swings away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
James Anderson serves a good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Much fuller this time, around off, at 136 clicks. Dean Elgar leans forward, closes the face of his bat, and blocks it out.
Slightly shorter on this occasion, swinging away, outside off. Dean Elgar blocks it out off the back foot.
Bowls a full-length delivery, angling in, around off. Dean Elgar strides forward and blocks it out towards point.
James Anderson pitches it up again, and maintains the same line outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward and defends it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Dean Elgar blocks it towards cover.
Back of a length, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
Good-length delivery, outside off, at 135 clicks. Sarel Erwee defends it out watchfully towards cover.
Swinging in this time, outside off, on a length, at 131 clicks. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
An out-swinger now, wide of off, fuller in length. Sarel Erwee watches it sail through to the keeper.
Wide! Fuller in length, wide of off, swinging further away. Sarel Erwee is happy to let that one go. Wide called!
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Matthew Potts comes over the wicket now, serves a length ball, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee offers no shot. That will be Lunch on Day 2!
Stuart Broad begins with a length ball, spraying it down leg. Dean Elgar looks to flick but he misses.
Much fuller this time, outside off, at 133 clicks. Dean Elgar miscues his drive towards the fielder at mid off.
Touch fuller again, outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward and pushes it towards cover.
Angling it in on this occasion, a length ball, outside off, at 133 clicks. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at it.
Pitches this one up, outside off, swinging in again, at 136 clicks. Dean Elgar strides forward and taps it towards the fielder at cover.
Fuller one, wide of off. Dean Elgar leans forward and drives it firmly through cover. Two taken!
Matthew Potts begins with a length ball from over the wicket, outside off. Sarel Erwee blocks it out.
Much straighter again, good-length delivery. Sarel Erwee blocks it out off the back foot.

Beaten! A beauty by Matthew Potts! This one lands on a length, nips back in, around middle and off. Sarel Erwee looks to block this one but he gets beaten on the inside edge. Still some movement there!
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Sarel Erwee does not fiddle with that one.
FOUR! Oh, good shot! Full in length, wide of off. Sarel Erwee lunges forward and creams his drives through cover-point for a boundary.

Edgy runs! Fuller again, wider this time. Sarel Erwee goes for the drive again, but the ball goes more off the outer half of his bat towards point. The fielder there manages to get a hand on that one. Two taken.
FOUR! Nicely done! Fuller in length, darting it on the pads. Dean Elgar uses his wrists and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length now, outside off. Dean Elgar defends it off the front foot.
Angling in now, back of a length, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar looks to flick this one but he misses and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Another out-swinger, tad shorter, outside off. Dean Elgar lets that go through to the keeper.
FOUR! Streaky boundary! Fuller one, wide of off. Dean Elgar prods forward and look tod rive tit away but he manages to get an outside edge away from gully and towards third man for a boundary.
FOUR! Glorious frim Sarel Erwee! An overpitched delivery, around middle and off. Sarel Erwee presents the full face of the bat and drives it down the ground away from mid off for a boundary.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
Back of a length, outside off again. Sarel Erwee offers no shot to that.

Sarel Erwee serves a length ball, around middle and off, extra bounce there as well. Sarel Erwee looks to block this one but the ball goes off his inside edge, onto the pads, and towards square leg. A single taken!
Change of angle now! Matthew Potts goes 'round the wicket and bowls a length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Beaten! Slightly short now, tighter line, around the fifth stump line. Dean Elgar stays in his crease and looks to block this but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, swinging away a tad, around middle. Sarel Erwee looks to work it away on the leg side, but the ball goes off the leading edge away from point for a couple of runs.
Shorter one, outside off, shaping away. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off again. Sarel Erwee watches it sail through to the keeper.

A length ball from over the wicket, angling down leg. Sarel Erwee misses his flick and the ball brushes off his thigh pad and goes towards the keeper. A stifled appeal there for caught behind but the umpire is not interested.
Good-length delivery, shaping away, wide of off. Sarel Erwee looks to have a poke at it but bails out in the end and leaves it alone.
Much straighter this time, firing it on the pads. Sarel Erwee tucks it towards square leg. No run there!
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar is happy to leave that alone.
Oh, well bowled! Tad slower this time, a length ball, angling in. Dean Elgar gets beaten on his inside edge while trying to block this one.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and width on offer this time, swinging away. Dean Elgar rocks back and slashes it past backward point for a boundary.
Wide of off again, touch short this time. Dean Elgar chops it off the back foot through point. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters pick up three runs.
FOUR! Second boundary in the over! This one is much fuller and on the pads. Sarel Erwee flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Pitches it up, outside off. Sarel Erwee drives this one firmly but finds the fielder at mid off. A good over for South Africa!
A length ball, swinging away, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Dean Elgar does not fiddle with that one.
Another length ball, tighter line this time, around the fifth stump line. Dean Elgar is happy to let it go.

An absolute ripper from Stuart Broad! This one lands on a length, it swings away after pitching, around the off pole. Dean Elgar looks to block this but he gets beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge.

Pulls his length back a tad, around middle. Dean Elgar looks to flick this one but he gets a leading edge towards the slip cordon. Ollie Pope at fourth slip collects the ball on a bounce and scores a direct hit at the striker's end. Dean Elgar was well in!
Fuller in length, width on offer. Dean Elgar strides forward and drives it through cover. Three taken!
Angling across, on a length from 'round the wicket, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
FOUR! Runs are flowing for South Africa at the moment! Full and firing it on the pads. Dean Elgar glances it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Matthew Potts drops it short now, around middle and off. Dean Elgar sways away from that one.
FOUR LEG BYES! More runs for South Africa! Another length ball, down leg. Dean Elgar misses his flick and the ball brushes off his pads and goes towards fine leg for a boundary.
Fuller ball, swinging in, down leg. Dean Elgar tucks it towards square leg and rotates the strike.
In the channel outside off, fuller in length. Sarel Erwee lets that go through to the keeper.

Anderson starts his new spell with an absolute cracker of a delivery! He bowls this on a fullish length and just around off. Elgar looks to drive it away but the ball swings away late and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Lands on a length, on off. Elgar blocks it off the front foot.
Angles it into middle and leg. Tad shorter as well and Elgar gets into an awkward position as he tries to defend it. The ball hits him high on the thigh pad.
Serves a length-delivery, outside off. Elgar leaves it alone nicely.
Jimmy goes tad fuller and it is around off. Elgar leans forward and drives it off the outside half of his blade through cover-point for a couple.
A big in-swinger to end the over! However, it starts from way outside off. Swings back in but still wide and Elgar is happy to let it go.
Angling into leg. A length delivery this and Erwee looks to clip it away. The ball hits his thigh pad and goes behind square on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar with a solid block from his crease.
Just short of good length, it is around off and Elgar punches it to covers.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tad shorter and it is around off. Elgar rides the bounce and punches it through cover-point for a boundary.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Elgar with an easy leave.

FOUR! Another boundary for Dean Elgar and South Africa are moving along nicely here! Stokes with a back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Elgar punches it through backward point and though the ball slows down near the fence, it still has enough wheels to reach the ropes as Pope puts in a big dive to stop it.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
On the shorter side, around off. Erwee punches it through covers for a single.

OUT! BOWLED! Oh, what an unlucky way to get out after playing so well. One of the most unfortunate dismissals you will see in cricket. Dean Elgar is gutted, he was looking so good and South Africa were almost running away with this game but luck shines for England and they get their first breakthrough. This one is tad shorter and angled into leg. Elgar looks to clip it away but misses. The ball hits his thigh pads and rolls back to the stumps. Elgar tries to stop the ball but is too late as the ball hits the stumps and the bail falls down on the pitch.
Howout: b James Anderson

Commentary: A fullish delivery, angling into middle. Keegan Petersen blocks it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! This is an inswinger that drifts on the pads. Keegan Petersen leans forward and glances it nicely past square leg for a boundary.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Back of a length and down the leg side. Erwee looks to clip it away but misses.
It is shorter in length and down the leg side again. Erwee is happy to let it go.
Another bouncer, this time better line. It is on middle and Erwee ducks under it.

Lovely delivery! This one is just short of good length and angled across the left-hander. Sarel Erwee looks to punch it away from his body and gets beaten as the ball zips past the outside edge of his blade.

FOUR! It's another good delivery but this time it is a boundary for South Africa. A fullish delivery, outside off. Erwee pushes at it. However, he gets a thick outside edge and the ball races through the gully region for a boundary.
Back of a length and outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
A fullish delivery, around off. Keegan Petersen plays it late and guides it through backward point for a couple.

Goes fuller, on off. Keegan Petersen drives it and initially hesitates to take a single. However, after the ball passes the short cover fielder, he calls for a run and Erwee after initially being late to react to that call runs across and it is an easy single in the end.
A  fullish delivery, around off. Erwee leans forward and creams it through covers for a couple.
On the shorter side and outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
Goes fuller and it is on the pads. Erwee looks to flick it but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls towards the leg side.

A big appeal for an LBW but it seems to be pitching outside leg. This is on a length and it is around leg. Sarel Erwee looks to defend but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal but the umpire is not interested.
Lands on a good length and it is outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
This time an outswinger that pitches, outside off. Keegan Petersen is happy to leave it alone.
Pulls his length back a bit, it is around off and Keegan Petersen makes another leave.

Ohh...that is a poor shot from Keegan Petersen! Stokes bowls it on a lovely length that is neither too short and neither full enough to drive. Keegan Petersen though goes for a big booming drive but gets beaten as the ball swings late and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, on middle. Keegan Petersen works it to mid-wicket.

FOUR LEG BYES! Anguish for Ben Stokes! He bowls a big in-swinger this time. It drifts on the pads and Keegan Petersen misses his flick shot. The ball brushes his pads and goes past the diving keeper for a boundary.
Shorter in length, on off. Erwee pulls it in front of square and comes back for the second run.
A fullish delivery that is outside off and Erwee leaves it alone.
Lands on a length, on off. Erwee is solid in defence this time.
Serves it on a length again, around off. Erwee is watchful again and blocks it away.
Jimmy goes tad fuller this time, on off. Hint of in-swing there but Erwee presents the full face of his blade and drives it back to the bowler.
James Anderson changes his angles and angles it on middle and leg from 'round the wicket. It is a length delivery and Sarel Erwee carefully defends it towards the leg side.
Goes fuller and down the leg side. Keegan Petersen looks to flick it but misses.
Stokes pulls his length back. It is around off this time and Keegan Petersen pushes it square off the wicket towards the off side for a single.
Goes fuller and it is angled into the pads. Erwee looks to clip it but misses and the ball brushes his pads on the way before going back to the keeper.
On a good length and outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
Just short of good length and it is outside off. Erwee plays it late and behind square towards the off side.
A short delivery and it is down the leg side. Erwee ducks under it.
Beaten! A typical Anderson outswinger. It starts from around off and swings away late to beat the outside edge of Keegan Petersen's blade as he looks to drive it away.
Pulls his length back a bit, it is outside off and Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Another outswinger, it is on a good length and outside off. Keegan Petersen lets it go again.

Now, this is the class of James Anderson! After bowling outswingers from the same line and length, he now delivers an inswinger. Keegan Petersen who leaves it is quite surprised to see that ball coming in sharply this time around.

This shot shows how much that last delivery left an impact on Keegan Petersen! James Anderson serves it on a good length and outside off. It swings away this time and Keegan Petersen goes for a wild swing across the line. He ends up getting beaten all ends up.
On a good length and outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone this time.
Potts goes fuller on off. Erwee leans forward and drives it straight down the ground for a couple as the fielder at mid off cuts it off.
This one is angled across the batter. It lands on a length and outside off. Erwee plays inside the line of the ball and lets it pass. The ball goes off the bounce to the keeper.
On a length and on off. The angle is taking that ball away from the left-hander again but Erwee manages to defend it off the outside half of his blade.
Tad fuller and around off. Erwee defends it off the front foot to the off side.
Goes straighter this time. It is fuller in length too and Erwee works it to mid-wicket.
Pulls his length back, on middle and leg. Erwee tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Tight single! A fuller one, shaping away, outside off, at 135 clicks. Sarel Erwee pushes it wide of mid off and scampers across to the other end.

EDGED AND FOUR! Stuart Broad drops this one short, outside off. Keegan Petersen stands tall and looks to punch this one to the off side. But the ball goes off the outside edge away from the slip cordon and towards third man for a boundary.
Another back-of-a-length delivery, maintains the same line outside off. Keegan Petersen taps it off the back foot towards cover-point for a single.
Fuller this time, around off. Sarel Erwee leans forward and drives it square of the wicket on the off side for a brace.
On a length now, outside off. Sarel Erwee blocks it out from within his crease.
A good-length delivery, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee tucks it towards square leg and takes a single. He retains the strike!
Angling in, a length ball from over the wicket, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee closes the face of his bat and flicks it through mid-wicket. A single!
Yorker-length delivery, outside the off pole. Keegan Petersen does well to dig this one out.
Matthew Potts pitches it up, swings away a tad, outside off. Keegan Petersen shoulders his arms at it.
Another full-length delivery, maintains the same line outside off, shaping away again. Keegan Petersen strides forward and leaves it alone.
Potts pulls his length back a tad, serves it on a length, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen gets a leading edge away from gully while trying to work it towards mid-wicket. Two taken!
Good-length delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen defends it out watchfully.
Stuart Broad pitches this one up, swings it away, outside off, at 135 clicks. Sarel Erwee does not fiddle with that one.
Jagging away again, outside off, fuller ball. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Another fuller ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee prods forward and pushes it towards mid off.

FOUR! Sarel Erwee brings up his fifty in style! Another fuller ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans forward and drives it square of the wicket to the off side. It's been a fine knock so far, he will be hoping to convert this into three figures.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
This one nips back in, on a length, around middle. Sarel Erwee looks to block this one but he gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Outside off, shaping away, a length ball. Left alone by Keegan Petersen.
Another out-swinger, length ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen dabs it towards cover-point. No run there!
FOUR! Gorgeous shot! A half-volley, outside off. Keegan Petersen lunges forward and creams his drive through cover for a beautiful boundary.
Pulls his length back now, tails this back in, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen tucks it towards square leg and rotates the strike.
Width on offer, fuller in length. Sarel Erwee taps it towards point with soft hands.
Matthew Potts drops it short, angling down leg, extra bounce there as well. Sarel Erwee misses his flick.
Fuller and straighter. Keegan Petersen tucks it towards square leg and takes a single.

Mix-up in the middle...but no harm done! A good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee stays in the crease and dabs it towards cover. Keegan Petersen leaves his crease for a single, but he is sent back by Sarel Erwee mid-way. Stuart Broad chases the ball and has a shy at the bowler's end, but he misses. Ben Stokes who was backing up misses the ball as well. It rolls away and the batters pick three runs at the end.
Outside off, good-length delivery. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Touch fuller this time, outside off again. Keegan Petersen is not interested in playing that.
Angling in, a fuller one, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen nudges it past short leg. Only a single.
Beaten! A peach by Stuart Broad! A good-length delivery, swinging away, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans to block this but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Matthew Potts overpitches this one, around off. Keegan Petersen knocks it past the diving mid on fielder for a brace. With that, the 50-run partnership comes up between these two.
A length ball, outside off, swinging away. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Another length ball, jagging away, wide of off. Keegan Petersen offers no shot once again.
A fuller one this time, outside off, swings away. Keegan Petersen strides forward and lets it go.
Pulls his length back now, tighter line as well, around the fourth stump line. Keegan Petersen is happy to leave it alone.
Oh, a beauty by Potts! Still no edge there. He serves it on a good length, and gets it to nip away a tad, outside off. Keegan Petersen is beaten as he tries to block this one out.
Slightly shorter this time, outside off. Sarel Erwee gets an inside edge onto his boot while trying to block this one.
On a good length, darting it on the pads. Sarel Erwee flicks it through square leg for a brace.
Swinging away, outside off, a length ball. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
Much fuller this time, outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards cover off the front foot.
Angling in, on a length, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee works it away towards mid-wicket.
A length ball from 'round the wicket, outside off, at 133 clicks. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! This time Matthew Potts gets his man! There is that edge he was looking for. A truly deserving wicket and Keegan Petersen has to walk back. A peach by Potts! He took some time to get his radar right but now seems to have found his rhythm back and is really bowling well here. This one is on a length, around the fourth stump line, shaping away. Keegan Petersen leans and looks to push this one away, but the ball goes off the outside edge towards third slip. Jonny Bairstow there, pouches it safely. England have their second wicket!
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Matthew Potts

Commentary: A length ball, outside off, swinging away. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
Another good-length delivery, outside off, swinging away. Aiden Markram opens the face of his bat and dabs it wide of gully for a brace. Aiden Markram is off the mark with that!
Outside off, on a length. Aiden Markram is happy to let that one go.
Matthew Potts serves a slightly shorter ball now, around middle. Aiden Markram blocks this one out from within his crease.
A good-length ball, outside off. Aiden Markram lets it go. A successful over from Potts comes to an end.
A JAFFA! What a bowl by James Anderson! It lands on a good length, nips away after pitching, around the fourth stump line. Sarel Erwee gets beaten on the outside edge while trying to block this one.
A length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee dabs it towards point and takes a single.
Tad fuller now, outside off. Aiden Markram pushes it towards cover-point and rotates the strike.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee taps it towards point and takes a single.
James Anderson serves it outside off, a length ball again. Aiden Markram offer no shot.
Fuller in length, swinging in, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee clips it towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Another fuller ball, outside off, shaping away. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Pitches it up again, darting it on the pads. Sarel Erwee clips it through square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Another full ball, wide of off this time. Aiden Markram takes a big stride forward and drives it crisply through cover for a boundary.
On a length now, nipping away, outside off. Aiden Markram is happy to let that one go.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Aiden Markram does not fiddle with that one.
Back of a length and around off. Erwee dabs it towards cover-point for a single.
Lands it on a good length and outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
Serves another delivery in that channel, outside off. Aiden Markram makes a good leave.
Jimmy is getting good swing here. This is on a length and around off. Aiden Markram is happy to let it go.

Now bowls a variation delivery. It is an inswinger that drifts on middle and leg. Aiden Markram looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits him high on the pads. There is a stifled appeal but nothing serious.
A fullish delivery, swinging into middle. Aiden Markram blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up, on off. Erwee blocks it off the front foot.
Nice turn for Leach! This one pitches around off and turns back in. Erwee looks to defend but gets beaten. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal but the impact is outside off.
Sarel Erwee uses his feet as Leach drags his length back a bit. It turns into the batter again and Erwee gets hit high on his pads.
Flaoted up nicely, on off. Erwee blocks it off the front foot.
This is around off again. Erwee leans forward and defends it with the angled blade towards point.
Pitches it fuller, on middle. Erwee defends it off the middle of his blade this time.
Back of a length and around off. Aiden Markram rides the bounce and dabs it towards point.
FOUR! Aiden Markram plays a glorious cover-drive now! Jimmy serves a half-volley, around off. Aiden Markram leans forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
A fullish delivery and nice shap away from the batter again. Aiden Markram looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A fuller delivery on middle. Aiden Markram flicks it through square leg for a single.
Lands it on a length, on off. Erwee blocks it solidly from his crease.
Leach is getting some good turn here. It is pitched around off and the ball turns away sharply as Aiden Markram leaves it.
Touch fuller and on off. Aiden Markram pushes it to covers.

FOUR! This is another classy shot from a classy batter! Leach pulls his length back by a bit and it is around off this time. Aiden Markram goes deep in his crease and punches it through cover-point for a boundary.
This is a bit quicker and close to off again. However, Aiden Markram decides to leave it this time.

Beaten! What a lovely delivery! This has been a good start from Leach. He tosses this up nicely and pitches it just short of full length, on off. Aiden Markram presses forward to defend but the ball turns away sharply and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Bowls a quicker delivery on middle. It is fuller and Aiden Markram works it to mid-wicket. South Africa are 158/2 at Tea on Day 2!
James Anderson starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee rides the bounce and punches it through cover-point for a couple.
Angles a length delivery, on off from 'round the wicket. Erwee defends it solidly off the front foot.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
Changes his length and bowls it fuller on off. Erwee drives but finds the mid off fielder.
Jimmy goes wide of the crease and angles it into middle. Erwee works it towards mid-wicket.
On the shorter side and around off. Erwee dabs it towards backward point.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Jack Leach strikes on his first delivery after Tea! He got some good turn and bowled quite well in those two overs he bowled before Tea and this really is a good decision by Stokes to start with the left-arm spinner along with James Anderson. This is a classic left-arm orthodox spinner's wicket. He flights this one nicely, lands it around off. It turns away a bit after pitching and takes the outside edge of Aiden Markram's blade as he looks to defend. Foakes takes a sharp catch behind the stumps and England have got a big breakthrough just after Tea.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Jack Leach

Commentary: NO BALL! It is a tossed up delivery, on off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it off the front foot. Leach oversteps here.
Pushes it quicker on off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out.
This one is tossed up and is around off. Rassie van der Dussen covers his off pole and lets it go.
Bowls it a tad flatter and quicker on off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out.
FOUR! Nicely played! Leach bowls it short and gives away a bit of width as well. Rassie van der Dussen goes deep in his crease and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Bowls it very full and fires it on middle. Rassie van der Dussen decides to block it this time.
Tad shorter and outside off. Erwee looks to cut it but misses. He needs to be more careful here.
Back of a length, on off. Erwee blocks it off the back foot.
Anderson goes wide of the crease and bowls it on a good length and outside off. The ball seams away after pitching and Erwee leaves it alone.
Goes tad fuller and around off. Erwee tries to drive it away but gets an inside half of his blade and the ball goes towards mid on.
Drifts on the pads. Erwee clips it towards right of fine leg and the batters run three.

Finds the edge but it is well short of the slip fielder. On a good length and around off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes at it away from his body. However, the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and falls short of the fourth slip fielder. Good thing was that he played it with soft hands.
A fullish delivery, around off. Erwee reverse-sweeps it. The ball though catches the top edge of his blade and runs towards the third man region. The batters take three.
On the shorter side and around off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Pushes it quicker and tad shorter again. Rassie van der Dussen lets it go again.
A fuller delivery on middle. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it off the front foot.
Slower through the air and on off. Rassie van der Dussen is well forward and defends it nicely.
A fuller delivery on middle. Rassie van der Dussen works it through mid-wicket and gets three runs.

FOUR! This is a good delivery from Stokes but Rassie van der Dussen will add another four runs to his score. On a good length and around off. Rassie van der Dussen tries to punch it away without much foot movement and gets the inside edge of his blade. The ball goes past stumps and runs away for a boundary towards the fine leg fence.
Back of a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it solidly off the back foot.
Touch short of full length and Rassie van der Dussen is tad early into his drive. The ball goes a bit aerially but it was quite well controlled in the end.
On a length, on middle. Rassie van der Dussen works it to mid-wicket.
Just short of good length and on off. There is a bit of extra bounce on this one and Rassie van der Dussen blocks it off the back foot.
A fullish delivery on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it off the front foot.
Leach pitches it around off and it turns in and hits Erwee high on his pads as he steps forward to defend it.
This is turning down leg but Erwee tries to sweep it. The ball bounce and gets hit on his arm. It loops up in the air and falls just away from the diving keeper.
A tossed up delivery on off. Erwee blocks it off the front foot.
Goes fuller on middle. Erwee sweeps it towards backward square leg. However, Potts does well to stop it with a dive.
Pitches it around off and it turns into Erwee who defends it off the front foot.
Another delivery that turns back in after pitching around off. Erwee is solid in his defence.
Good-length delivery, swinging away, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Angling in this time, another length ball, around middle and leg. Rassie van der Dussen tucks it towards square leg. No run there!
Ben Stokes serves a length ball again, shaping away, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen offers no shot to that.
Very full this time, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen taps it towards point.
A full toss this time, wide of off. Rassie van der Dussen is not interested in playing that one.
Pitches it up again, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen is happy to let that go through to the keeper.
Tosses this one up, full and turning in. Sarel Erwee heaves it over mid-wicket. Alex Lees runs across from deep square leg and makes a good stop there. Two taken.
Shorter ball, turning in, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee stays in his crease and looks to push this one away, but the ball goes off his inside edge through his legs and towards short fine leg.
A fuller ball, loopy one, around middle. Sarel Erwee leans forward and blocks it out.
Back of a length, around middle and leg, turning in. Sarel Erwee uses the depth of her crease flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Tosses this one up, full, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen lunges forward and defends it out.
Another pitched-up delivery, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen leans forward and blocks it out.
Ben Stokes comes from 'round the wicket and serves a short ball, angling down leg. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Another back-of-a-length delivery, down leg again. Sarel Erwee ducks and lets it go through to the keeper.
Ben Stokes hits the deck hard again and serves it around middle and off. Sarel Erwee ducks undeneath it.
Ben Stokes sticks to his shorter length deliveries, around middle. Sarel Erwee is happy to duck under that one.
Ben Stokes bangs it short, outside this time. Sarel Erwee sways away from that one.
Back of a length, angling in, on the body. Sarel Erwee fends it towards short leg. Ollie Pope there dives and makes a good stop.
Tosses this one up, full, around off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out off the front foot.
Another loopy ball, spinning away, outside off, fuller one. Rassie van der Dussen prods forward and blocks it out.
Slower through the air, full, around off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it off the front foot.
This one comes in with the arm, quicker, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen stays in his crease and blocks it out.
FOUR! Top shot! A fuller one, tosses it up, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen gets down on his knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.
Slower through the air, full, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen shows the full face of the bat and defends it out.
Ben Stokes bowled 6 short balls in his previous over and starts this over with another shorter one, outside off. Sarel Erwee punches it off the back foot towards cover for a brace.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ben Stokes' plan to bowl short balls has finally worked! The skipper gets rid of a well-set batter here. A big wicket for England and a much-needed one as well. Ben Stokes serves a nasty bouncer, around middle. Sarel Erwee hops and tries to get away from that one. But the ball goes off his glove and lobs up towards the keeper. Ben Foakes backtracks and takes a simple catch. Sarel Erwee departs after a fine knock of 73.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Ben Stokes goes 'over the wicket now, serves another short ball, down leg. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Marco Jansen pushes it off the back foot towards point for a single. Marco Jansen gets off the mark.
FOUR! Pulled away! Back of a length, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen slaps this one through square leg for a boundary.
Shorter ball again, down leg. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Tossed up delivery, full and around off. Marco Jansen leans forward and defends it out.
Shorter one, spinning away, outside off. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Jack Leach flights this one, serves it full and around off. Marco Jansen presses forward and blocks it out.
Another loopy ball, pitches it up, around off. Marco Jansen drives it towards mid off.
Slower through the air, full, around middle and leg. Marco Jansen presses forward and defends it out.
