Another full ball, slower through the air, around off. Marco Jansen prods forward and defends this one.
A length ball, spraying it down leg. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.

OUT! LBW! Ben Stokes has done it again! Two wickets in two overs for the skipper! He sends Rassie van der Dussen back to the hut. A length ball, this one nips back in after pitching, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen looks to flick this one but he misses and gets rapped on his front pad. A loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger immediately. Rassie van der Dussen though opts for a review. No bat involved there, confirms UltraEdge. The Ball Tracking indicates three reds. Not a great review from Rassie van der Dussen as that looked quite straight.
Howout: lbw b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Back of a length, around middle. Kyle Verreynne looks to defend this one but misses and gets hit on his body.
Another shorter ball, darting it on the thigh pad. Kyle Verreynne tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Ben Stokes serves it short again, down leg. Marco Jansen fends it towards square leg. A single taken.
No ball! On a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone. A no ball is called as Ben Stokes has overstepped here.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne taps it towards point.
Loopy ball, full, around middle. Marco Jansen pushes it towards mid on and takes a single.
FOUR! Poor ball and punished! A shorter one now, spinning away, around off. Kyle Verreynne uses the depth of his crease and cuts it past point for a boundary.
Flatter, straighter, around middle and off. Kyle Verreynne defends it out.
Tosses it up, full, and around off. Kyle Verreynne lunges forward and defends it out.
Shorter one this time, turning away, around off. Kyle Verreynne pushes it off the back foot towards mid off.
A loopy ball, full, slower through the air, around middle. Kyle Verreynne leans forward and defends it out.
Stuart Broad starts off with a length ball, around the off pole. Marco Jansen leans forward and blocks it out.
On a length now, outside off, at 131 clicks. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Angling in, another length ball, at 138 clicks. Marco Jansen leans forward to block this one but the ball goes off his inside edge onto his pads.
Good-length delivery, tailing back in, around off, at 132 clicks. Marco Jansen defends it out.
NO BALL! Back of a length, outside off, swinging away. Marco Jansen gets beaten while trying to block this one. Stuart Broad have overstepped here and a no ball is called.
A length ball, nipping back in, around off. Marco Jansen blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, angling in, around off, at 130 clicks. Marco Jansen keeps it out.
Shorter ball, spinning away, around off. Kyle Verreynne punches it off the back foot towards cover. The fielder there dives to his left and makes a good stop.
A loopy ball, full, around, around middle. Kyle Verreynne blocks it towards mid on.
Tosses it up again, around middle, fuller in length. Kyle Verreynne defends it out.
Edgy runs! Tosses this one up, full, it lands around middle and leg, and spins away. Kyle Verreynne leans to block this one but the ball goes off his inside edge towards square leg for a single.
Floats it up, full, around middle. Marco Jansen pushes it towards mid on.
Another loopy ball, full, around off. Marco Jansen leans forward and defends it out.
A fullish delivery angling into middle. Kyle Verreynne goes across his crease and gets his bat down in time and works it towards mid on for a single.
A fuller delivery, on off. Jansen drives it to covers for a single.
On a good length and jagging into middle. Kyle Verreynne wrists it to mid-wicket for a single.
A bouncer from Broad, around off. Jansen ducks under it.

Lands on a length, on off. Jansen is solid in his defence. This man has the ability to bat and has been trusted by the team management to bat up the order. Can he deliver and take his team to a big lead here?
A fuller delivery on off. Jansen drives it just past Broad for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle. Jansen steps down and pushes it down the ground for a single.
Slower through the air, on off. Kyle Verreynne drives it to covers.
Tad shorter on off. Kyle Verreynne uses the depth of the crease and punches it to covers.
Bowls an arm delivery. It is flatter and on middle. Kyle Verreynne blocks it off the back foot.

Kyle Verreynne goes for a big shot and almost fell in the trap there. A fuller delivery, around off. Kyle Verreynne skips down the track and goes for a powerful shot. He mistimes it but gets enough to hit it away from Stokes at covers and gets three runs as the fielder cuts it off near the fence.
A flatter delivery on off. Jansen blocks it off the front foot.
A full delivery on middle. Kyle Verreynne blocks it towards the mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Stuart Broad gets his 100th wicket at Lord's! What an achievement this is, tells a lot about the skills and fitness of the guy. He gets to this landmark with a peach of a delivery. Serves it on a good length and around off. Kyle Verreynne is trapped in his crease and pokes at it tentatively. The ball seams away a tad after pitching and catches the outside edge of Kyle Verreynne's blade. The ball goes straight into the hands of Foakes and he takes it comfortably. Six down now South Africa!
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Broad welcomes Keshav Maharaj with a bouncer. On off and Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.
Bangs it short again, around leg. Maharaj is happy to duck under it again.
Looks like England and Broad have some plan for Keshav Maharaj. Broad with another short-pitch delivery that is well handled by Keshav Maharaj by ducking again.
Broad comes 'round the wicket and bowls another bouncer, on middle. Keshav Maharaj does what he has been doing in his first three balls.
Back of a length, around off. Jansen waits for it and guides it to third man for a single.
Potts bowls a bouncer and it drifts down the leg side. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.
All Keshav Maharaj has done in his short stay in the middle is to duck under the ball and he does that again as he recieves another short ball.
On the shorter side and down the leg side. Keshav Maharaj watches it go past him.
Back of a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj with a solid block off the back foot.
Short and around leg. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.
Finds the edge but it goes between Foakes and Root who is standing at almost third slip there. Luckily for England, the third man is fine and it is just a single.
A fullish delivery, on off. Keshav Maharaj drives it to covers for a single.
Bangs it short on off. Jansen ducks under it.
Broad comes 'round the wicket now and bowls it on the shorter side again. On middle and Jansen works it to fine leg for a single.
Bangs it short again, on middle. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it. Not sure this ploy of bowling short on almost every delivery is working for England here.
On a length, on middle. Keshav Maharaj works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Better from Potts! Lands it on a good length, on middle. Keshav Maharaj blocks it from his crease.
He is back to bowling short, on off. Keshav Maharaj sways away from the line of the ball.

A bouncer on middle and Keshav Maharaj ducks under it. Just getting a feeling that England need to go back to the basics here. This pitch has enough for the bowlers if they bowl good lines and lengths.
Bangs it short on middle. Keshav Maharaj pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Lands on a length, on middle. Jansen is solid in his defence.
On a length, on middle. Jansen is good enough to block it off the middle of his blade.

FOUR! Broad goes back to his basics and finds an edge. However, Keshav Maharaj has got away with this one. A good-length delivery, outside off. Keshav Maharaj tries to punch it towards the off side but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes past the third slip fielder for a boundary.
Bangs it short on middle. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Keshav Maharaj! Short and wide outside off. Keshav Maharaj hangs on his back foot and cuts it in front of square for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Keshav Maharaj rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
On a length and outside off. Keshav Maharaj pushes it right of point for a single.
On a length, on middle. Jansen works it towards mid-wicket for a single. 10 runs from the over and the lead is now 61!
Beaten! Serves a good-length delivery, It is close to off and Jansen gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to push it away.
Goes fuller on off. Jansen drives it to covers.
On a length, around off. Jansen dabs it towards point. Looks like Potts is done with his short-pitch stuff.
Oops! I think I made that judgement a bit too early. Potts bangs it short on middle and Jansen will be very happy as he ducks under it.
A fuller delivery, around off. Jansen drives it to covers this time.
Bowls it very full on off. Jansen blocks it out towards the off side.
Tad shorter and on off. Keshav Maharaj goes deep in his crease and cuts it to point.
Tossed up, on off. Keshav Maharaj defends it off the front foot.
Pulls his length back a bit, around off and Keshav Maharaj punches it to covers.
Bowls it quicker on middle. It is flatter as well and Keshav Maharaj gets hit on his pads as he tries to defend it.
A fuller delivery on middle. Keshav Maharaj goes for a big shot down the ground but does not time it that well and ends up hitting it along the ground wide of long on for a single.
Ohh...that almost went through! An arm ball that pitches on off and comes in with the angle. Jansen looks to defend it but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Back of a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! These are crucial runs for South Africa! Back of a length and around off. Keshav Maharaj cuts it through the gully region for a boundary.
On a length, on middle. Keshav Maharaj nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
On the shorter side and outside off. Jansen rides the bounce and pushes it to point.

FOUR! Second boundary of the over and this is turning out to be a nice little partnership for South Africa! Overpitched delivery, outside off. Jansen leans forward and drives it through cover-point for a boundary.
Bouncer to end the over, on off and Jansen ducks under it.
Tosses it up, full, around middle and leg, at 87 clicks. Keshav Maharaj leans to block this one but he gets an inside edge towards square leg.
Another fuller ball, loopy one as well, around off. Keshav Maharaj blocks it out.
Tad quicker, at around 91 clicks, full again, around off. Keshav Maharaj gets an inside edge back onto his pads while trying to block this one.
Tossed up ball, around middle, full in length. Keshav Maharaj dances down the pitch and heaves it over mid-wicket for three runs.
Slower through the air, fuller ball, around off. Marco Jansen prods forward and defends it out.
FOUR! Up and over! Another pitched-up delivery, around middle and off. Marco Jansen shimmies down the pitch and tonks it over mid on for a boundary.
James Anderson begins with a length ball, wide of off. Keshav Maharaj cuts it towards the fielder at cover.
Back of a length again, outside off. Keshav Maharaj pushes it off the back foot through cover this time. Two taken.
Angling in, on a length, around off. Keshav Maharaj blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely done! James Anderson drops it short again, and offers width as well. Keshav Maharaj punches it off the back foot through cover-point for a boundary.
FOUR! Crunched! Lovely shot from Keshav Maharaj once again. Back of a length, around middle. Keshav Maharaj pulls it powerfully over mid-wicket for a cracking boundary.
Much fuller now, outside off. Keshav Maharaj drives it firmly but finds the fielder at mid off.
Ben Stokes starts off with a shorter ball, around off. Marco Jansen sways away from that one.

Ben Stokes drops it short again, outside off. Marco Jansen stays in his crease and punches it off the back foot through cover. The ball will go towards the boundary, but there is enough time for the batters to pick up four runs.
Another short one, outside off. Marco Jansen pushes it towards long off. No fielder there, Ben Stokes chases the ball and keeps it to two runs.
Another short ball, down the leg side. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
SIX! Bang! Ben Stokes serves yet another short ball, around middle. Marco Jansen pulls it high over fine leg for a biggie. That brings up the 50-run stand between these two.
FOUR! Marco Jansen takes the aerial route once again! A length ball, around middle. Marco Jansen hoicks this one over mid-wicket for a boundary. 16 runs off the over.
Fuller in length, around middle and off. Keshav Maharaj defends it out.
Beaten this time! A length ball, outside off. Keshav Maharaj looks to push this away but he misses.
FOUR! Runs are flowing for South Africa now! Short ball, outside off. Keshav Maharaj punches it off the back foot through point for a boundary.
Pitches it up again, outside off. Keshav Maharaj drives it towards cover.
Play and a miss! Slower one, outside off. Keshav Maharaj stays in his crease and looks to cut this away but he misses.
FOUR! Short ball again and punished again! This is outside off. Keshav Maharaj rocks back and punches it through cover for a boundary.
Short ball, around middle. Marco Jansen pulls it over mid-wicket. Three taken.
Bangs it short, around middle and off. Keshav Maharaj pulls it over mid on for a brace.
Sticks to his length, serves another short one, down the leg side. Keshav Maharaj leaves it alone.
Spraying it down the leg side again, back of a length. Keshav Maharaj lets it go.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, England have managed to break this stand and it's the skipper once again who strikes. A good cameo from Keshav Maharaj comes to an end. Ben Stokes drops it short, around middle this time, cramping Keshav Maharaj for room there. Keshav Maharaj goes for the pull shot but the ball goes off the top edge and lobs up towards mid-wicket. Matthew Potts there takes a good catch over his head. Ben Stokes has third and England have got their seventh wicket.
Howout: c Matthew Potts b Ben Stokes

Commentary: A length ball, darting it on the thigh pad. Kagiso Rabada tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Jack Leach comes over the wicket, serves a shorter one, spinning in, around middle. Kagiso Rabada blocks it out.
Tosses this one up, full, around middle. Kagiso Rabada leans forward and defends it out.
Quicker this time, coming in with the arm, around middle. Kagiso Rabada blocks it towards short leg.
Tosses this one up, full and outside off. Kagiso Rabada drives it towards cover. James Anderson there dives to his right and makes a good stop.
A loopy ball, full, around middle. Kagiso Rabada blocks it towards mid-wicket.
Edged and away! Shorter ball, spinning in, around off. Kagiso Rabada stays in his crease and looks to block this but the ball goes off the outside edge away from the fielder at first slip. Two taken!
A shorter ball, around middle. Marco Jansen ducks under it.
Shorter ball, around off. Marco Jansen blocks it out off the back foot.
Spraying it down leg, shorter one. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Angling in, another short ball, around middle. Marco Jansen blocks it out towards square leg.

FOUR! Punished! Ben Stokes drops it short again, around middle and leg. Marco Jansen swivels and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket. Jonny Bairstow runs to his left, and dives but he fails to stop the ball. A boundary!
Shorter ball, down leg. Marco Jansen leaves it alone. That will be Stumps on Day 2!
Starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Rabada leaves it alone.
Bowls a bouncer around leg this time. Rabada ducks under it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh, what a stunning catch from Stuart Broad! A perfect start for England on Day 3! Matthew Potts strikes in his first over of the day and gets rid of Kagiso Rabada. Another short ball, around off. Kagiso Rabada stays in his crease and miscues his pull shot towards mid on. Stuart Broad there, backtracks sticks his right hand up in the air, and takes a terrific catch. That looked like it was going over him for a boundary! Stuart Broad, you beauty!
Howout: c Stuart Broad b Matthew Potts

Commentary: Back of a length, outside off. Anrich Nortje leaves it alone.
Matthew Potts hits the deck hard once again, around middle and off. Anrich Nortje ducks under it and leaves it alone.
Matthew Potts sticks to bowling his short ball, and sprays this one down leg. Anrich Nortje leaves it alone. A wicket-maiden to begin proceedings on Day 3!
Ben Stokes begins with a short ball, angling in, around middle. Marco Jansen blocks it out off the back foot.
On a length this time, tailing back in, around middle. Marco Jansen dabs it towards square leg.
Good-length delivery, darting this on on this thigh pad. Marco Jansen flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Bangs it short, around middle. Anrich Nortje ducks under this one.
Bowls a short delivery that is around leg. Anrich Nortje ducks under it.
This is a well-directed bumper. Angling into the body and Nortje manages to block it onto the turf nicely in the end.
Pitches it up this time, outside off. Marco Jansen prods forward and gets beaten while trying to drive this one.
On a length, much straighter this time. Marco Jansen pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Another well-directed bumper from Matthew Potts. Anrich Nortje ducks underneath it.
Wide of off this time, a shorter ball. Anrich Nortje leaves it alone.
Beaten! A shorter ball, outside off. Anrich Nortje looks to have a poke at that one but he misses.
Matthew Potts goes 'round the wicket now and serves another short ball. Anrich Nortje ducks and leaves it alone.
Lands on a length, outside off. Jansen lets it go.
A fullish delivery, around off. Jansen pushes it to covers for a single.
A short ball and around off. Anrich Nortje sways away from the line of the ball.
On the shorter side again, on off. Anrich Nortje rides the bounce and blocks it out.
This is shorter in length and around off. Nortje looks to defend but gets the outside edge of his blade as this ball hurries him. The ball goes in the air but over the gully fielder for a single.
A length delivery, on off. Jansen blocks it.
Shorter in length, angling into leg. Anrich Nortje works it away to short leg for a single.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Jansen has a poke at it but gets beaten.
Lands on a length and outside off. Jansen leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Jansen tries to push it away but misses.
On a length, around off. Jansen blocks it out.
A good-length delivery, outside off. This one keeps a bit low and beatsb Jansen as he looks to defend it.
Back of a length, around leg. Anrich Nortje makes room and blocks it out watchfully.
Ben Stokes serves a short ball, down leg. Anrich Nortje looks to pull this one but he misses.
Bye! Ben Stokes errs in line again and spills it way down leg. Anrich Nortje leaves it alone. Ben Foakes dives but fails to stop the ball. A bye taken.
On a length, outside off this time. Marco Jansen leans forward and pushes it towards the fielder at mid off.
Shorter ball, down leg. Anrich Nortje backs away and does well to fend it towards the leg side.
Outside off, another bouncer from Ben Stokes. Anrich Nortje jumps to block this one but leaves it alone in the end.
Serves a length delivery on middle. Jansen works it to deep backward square leg for a single.

FOUR! In the air...but just away from Zak Crawley at the third man region. Potts bowls it short and around off. Nortje makes room and throws his bat at it. The ball goes off the outside edge of his blade and in the air towards third man. Crawley runs forward and to his right but fails to reach it and the ball runs away towards the fence.
On the shorter side, on off. Nortje punches it to cover-point for a single.
A fuller delivery on middle. Jansen works it through mid-wicket for a single.
Potts bowls it short, around off as well. Anrich Nortje leaves it alone.
Short delivery and outside off. Anrich Nortje goes for the upper-cut. He, however, ends up hitting it towards deep extra-cover. The batters take three.
Back of a length, on leg. Nortje rides the bounce and works it to backward square leg for a single.
Lovely good-length delivery, around off. Jansen tries to defend it but the ball seams away a bit and zips past the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, on leg. Jansen looks to work it towards the leg side. However, he misses and the ball rolls towards the leg side off his pads. A leg bye taken.
Stokes bangs it short, on middle. Nortje ducks under it.
Goes wide of the crease and angles a length delivery on middle. Nortje works it to fine leg for a single.
Bowls a short delivery and it is down the leg side. Jansen lets it go.
Back of a length, on middle. Nortje blocks it off the back foot.
Broad with a short delivery, outside off. Nortje makes room and cuts it towards deep extra cover. The ball goes in the air but there is no one there in the deep. Another three added to the score.
Shorter in length, on off. Jansen pushes it to covers for a single.
Serves a length delivery on off. Nortje tries to defend it but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
A fuller delivery and it drifts on the pads. Nortje works it to square leg for a single.
Pulls his length back a bit, around off. Jansen defends it towards the off side. It is quite surprising to see England bowling short even after taking the new ball.
On a length, on off. Anrich Nortje blocks it out.
FOUR! Very confident shot from Nortje! Goes fuller on off. Nortje shows the full face of his blade and drives it past mid on for a boundary.
Back of a length and angling into leg. Nortje works it towards the leg side.
On a length, on middle. Nortje is comfortable to defend it. It has been 40 balls since the new ball has been taken but still no signs of James Anderson.
Keeps it short and around off. Nortje leaves it alone.

A nasty bouncer this time but it is really well played by Nortje! A short delivery angling into off. Nortje rides the bounce and blocks it towards the off side as he takes his one hand off the handle.

OUT! CAUGHT! This is what happens when you pitch the ball up with the new ball. England took some time to release it but Broad finally gets his length right and takes an important wicket of Marco Jansen. A brilliant knock from the young man though and he deserved to get his fifty but that's how the game works and he walks back to a standing ovation here. This is a fullish delivery, outside off. Not that full to go for a big booming drive but Jansen does and gets an outside edge of his blade. The ball goes straight into the hands of Zak Crawley at second slip and South Africa are nine down now.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Stuart Broad

Commentary: On a length and outside off. Lungi Ngidi leaves it.
This is also on a length and outside off. Lungi Ngidi makes an easy leave.
Bangs it short now, around leg. Lungi Ngidi ducks under it.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Lungi Ngidi plays it inside the line of the ball as the ball shapes away late.
Goes fuller and down the leg side. Lungi Ngidi looks to clip it but misses.
Swinging in late and drifting on the pads. Nortje looks to clip it away but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls towards the off side.
On the shorter side, angling into pads. Nortje looks to works it towards the leg side but misses again. The ball hits him high on the pads.
FOUR! This is turning out to be a very handy knock from Anrich Nortje. Back of a length, around off. Anrich Nortje stays leg side of the ball and guides it through the gully region for a boundary.
FOUR! Stokes kicks the ground in frustration. This is fuller and around off. Anrich Nortje manages to power it through extra-cover for a boundary.
Back of a length, on middle. Anrich Nortje looks to guide it towards the off side but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Anrich Nortje throws his bat at it but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jonny Bairstow takes the catch at third slip, he almost made a mess of it but shows good reflexes in the end to complete the catch with his left hand. Broad bowls a fullish delivery, outside off. Lungi Ngidi tries to drive it away but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes at a good height and straight to Jonny Bairstow at third slip. However, he fails to pouch it on one go but then takes it with his left hand bending quite low. He looks like a relieved man after taking that catch and rightly so, England are already way behind in this game and they cannot afford to miss these kind of chances. South Africa are all-out on 326!
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Kagiso Rabada begins with a length ball, shaping away, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Alex Lees stays in his crease and blocks it out.
A length ball, swinging away, outside off. Alex Lees watches it sail through to the keeper.
Shorter ball, outside off. Alex Lees stays in his crease and looks to cut this away but he gets an under edge back onto the deck.
A fuller one this time, around middle and off. Alex Lees blocks it out.
Another one outside the off pole, a length ball. Alex Lees is happy to let that one go.

Lungi Ngidi begins with a length ball, tailing back in, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley looks to flick this one but he misses and gets rapped on his pads. A loud appeal there for LBW, but the umpire says no. Sliding down leg probably.
Another on that nips back in, a length ball, around middle. Zak Crawley defends it out.
Sharp swing there once again! A shorter ball, outside off, swinging in. Zak Crawley leaves it alone. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left and makes a lovely stop. Good movement there!
Swinging in, around middle, a length ball. Zak Crawley tucks it towards square leg for a brace. Zak Crawley and England are underway!
Pitches it up, much straighter on this occasion, around middle. Zak Crawley blocks it out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Zak Crawley stays in his crease and pushes it off the back foot towards cover for a single. A lovely over Lungi Ngidi! He made the ball talk a lot in his first over.
Rabada lands it on a length, on off. Crawley works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
FOUR! Beautifully played! He is off the mark with a boundary. Rabada keeps it tad shorter and around off. Lees gets on top of the bounce and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Beaten! Rabada continues to bowl that length which is just short of good length. It is around off and Lees tries to defend it but the ball seams away and beats the outside edge of his blade.

Ohh...dropped! This is a full delivery, around off. Lees tries to drive it away. However, the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and is travelling straight to Aiden Markram at second slip. Keegan Petersen at third slip dives in front of Aiden Markram and ends up getting one hand to it but the ball does not stick. A single taken as the ball goes behind them.
On a length, on off. Zak Crawley pushes it to covers for a single.
On a good length and outside off. Lees leaves it alone.
An in-swinger, a good-length delivery, around middle. Zak Crawley covers the line and blocks the ball.
Another ball tailing back in from a good length, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Lungi Ngidi comes 'round the wicket now, serves a length ball, around middle and off. Alex Lees defends it out.
Oh, well bowled! A fuller one this time, jagging back in sharply, around middle and leg. Alex Lees looks to block this one but he manages to get a slight inside edge back onto his pads.

Another ripper from Lungi Ngidi! This is lovely bowling from him. On a length, shaping away a tad, around off. Alex Lees leaves it alone. The ball misses the off pole by a whisker. Tight leave from Alex Lees.
Fuller ball this time, outside off. Alex Lees blocks it out. Another testing over from Lungi Ngidi comes to an end.
Slightly shorter, around middle and leg, extra bounce there as well. Zak Crawley looks to tuck it on the leg side, but the ball goes off the leading edge towards cover.

Another edge! On a length this time, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley looks to flick this one but the ball goes off the leading edge again once again, away from the fielder at cover this time. Two taken.
Angling in, fuller one, darting it on the pads. Zak Crawley flicks it through square leg for a single.
Outside off this time, fuller ball. Alex Lees drives it towards the fielder at cover.
Angling away, shorter one, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Beaten! Lovely ball! Slightly short again, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees looks to push this away but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
A good-length ball, on the pads. Zak Crawley looks to flick this one but the ball flies over mid-wicket off the leading edge. Anrich Nortje chases the ball and keeps it two runs.
Fuller ball, swinging in, around middle. Zak Crawley blocks it out towards the leg side.
Outside off, a length ball. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Another good-length delivery, the line is outside off. Zak Crawley leans forward and lets that go through.
This one swings back in, fuller in length, around off, at 143 clicks. Zak Crawley drives and finds the fielder at short cover.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Zak Crawley strides forward and shoulders his arms at it.
On a length from over the wicket, nipping back in. Alex Lees manages to get an inside edge onto his pads while trying to flick this one.
Shaping away this time, outside off, on a length. Alex Lees offers no shot to that.
Width on offer now, full in length. Alex Lees frees his arms and drives it through cover. Two taken.
Tighter line now! Around the off pole, a length ball, at 140 clicks. Alex Lees pushes it towards the fielder at mid off.
Another length ball, outside off. Alex Lees punches it off the back foot towards point.
Swing and a miss! Kagiso Rabada drops it short, shaping away, outside off. Alex Lees goes for the pull shot but he fails to get any bat on it.
Keshav Maharaj comes from 'round the wicket, serves a fuller one, loopy as well, at 87 clicks. Zak Crawley defends it out off the front foot.
Quicker, full, darting it on the pads. Zak Crawley shimmies down the pitch and flicks it towards mid-wicket. Two taken!

OUT! LBW! Keshav Maharaj strikes in his first over of the game! He gets rid of Zak Crawley and his poor run of form continues. What a move to bring Keshav Maharaj on! He tosses this one up, fuller one, tad slower through the air, on middle. Zak Crawley gets down on his knee and looks to sweep this one but he misses and gets hit on his pad. A loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger without any hesitation. South Africa have got their first wicket.
Howout: lbw b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary: Shorter ball, spinning away, around off. Ollie Pope uses the depth of his crease and pushes it towards cover.
Much fuller now, on the pads. Ollie Pope flicks it through mid-wicket for a single. Ollie Pope is off the mark!

Keshav Maharaj comes 'over the wicket to the left-hander now, serves a shorter one, turning in, around middle and leg. Alex Lees tucks it towards mid-wicket. End of a successful first over from Keshav Maharaj.
Beaten! Good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope gets beaten on his outside edge while trying to block this one.
FOUR BYES! Bonus runs for England! A shorter ball, down leg. Ollie Pope leaves it alone. Kyle Verreynne dives but he fails to get there as well. It runs away towards fine leg for a boundary.
On a length, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope opens the face of his bat and guides it past gully for a brace.
Angling in, a length ball, around middle. Ollie Pope works it away towards mid on for a single.
Outside off, nipping away, a length ball. Alex Lees leaves it alone.

Nice shot! An overpitched delivery, around off. Alex Lees shows the full face of his blade and drives it down the ground. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters pick up three runs.
A loopy ball, spinning in, outside off. Alex Lees takes a big stride forward and looks to block this but he gets an inside edge back onto his pads.
A shorter one now, quicker as well, around middle. Alex Lees skips down the pitch and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tosses this one up, serves it full and outside off., Alex Lees lunges forward to block this one but he misses and gets hit on his body.
Floats it up again, full and around middle. Alex Lees sweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
Keshav Maharaj goes 'round the wicket now, serves a shorter one this time, this one comes in with the angle as well. Ollie Pope stays in his crease and tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Quicker, turning into the left-hander, around middle. Alex Lees works it away towards mid-wicket.

FOUR LEG BYES! Kagiso Rabada serves this one down leg, a length ball. Ollie Pope looks to flick this one but he misses. The ball brushes off his pads and goes away from diving fielder towards fine leg for a boundary.
A length ball, nipping back in sharply, around off. Ollie Pope shoulders his arm at this one. The ball hits his thigh pad and goes towards the slip cordon.
Another out-swinger, outside off, a length ball. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
On a length, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope blocks it out.
Shorter one, outside off, shaping away. Ollie Pope dabs it towards point.
Back of a length, shaping back in this time, around off. Ollie Pope does well to block this one.

Dropped! But those chances are always tough! A shorter one, spinning in, around middle and leg. Alex Lees stays in his crease and flicks it towards short leg. The fielder there gets his hands to the ball but fails to hold on to it.
Quicker one, short again, spinning in. Alex Lees defends it out off the back foot.
Tosses this one up, full, around off. Alex Lees blocks it out.
Back of a length, around middle and leg, spinning in. Alex Lees flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Loopy ball, full, around off. Ollie Pope leans forward and defends it out.

OUT! LBW! A wicket for South Africa on the final ball before Lunch! Keshav Maharaj, who did not bowl one over in the first innings, has now picked up two wickets in the second innings. He sends back Ollie Pope now. This is a big, big wicket for South Africa and England are under pressure early in the innings. Coming to the ball - this was a shorter one, it comes in with the arm, on the leg pole. Ollie Pope rocks back and looks to flick this one but he misses and gets rapped on his pads. A loud appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no. Dean Elgar though decides to review this one. No bat involved there, confirms UltraEdge. The Ball Tracking indicates, three reds. The decision needs to be overturned and Ollie Pope has to depart. A successful review for South Africa. That will be Lunch on Day 3.
Howout: lbw b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary: Ngidi starts off with a length delivery, outside off. Lees lets it go.
Lands it on a length, on off. Lees with a solid block from his crease.
Bowls it fuller and wider outside off. Lees drives it off the bottom of his blade towards point.
An inside edge this time! On a length, around off. Lees tries to push it towards the off side but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
A fullish delivery, around off. Lees pushes it to covers this time.
Angles this full delivery on the pads. Lees flicks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
A flatter delivery turning into middle. Lees stands tall and pushes it to mid on for a single.
Nice flighted delivery, on off. Root blocks it off the front foot.
Root uses his feet and drives this full delivery on off to mid off.
Slower through the air, on middle. Root with a solid front foot defence.
He is off the mark. This is fuller, on off. Root drives it through covers for a single.
Bowls it bit quicker on middle. Lees works it towards midwicket.
Serves it on a length, around off. It jags back in and Root defends it towards point for a single.
EDGED AND FOUR! On a good length and outside off. Alex Lees stands tall and looks to punch this away but the ball goes off the outside in the gap between third slip and gully for a boundary.
Goes fuller on off. Lees drives it through covers and comes back for the second run.
Fuller length, outside off. Lees cuts it towards the point region.
On the shorter side, around off. Lees tries to pull it but gets the inside edge. The ball goes just past stumps and the keeper makes a good stop diving to his right.
That ball was on the pads and Alex Lees just guides it towards the fine leg region for a single.
This one pitches on middle and turns down the leg side. Lees tries to work it towards the leg side but misses.
Tossed up, on middle. Lees defends it off the front foot.
Turning into middle. Lees works it towards mid-wicket.
Turning into leg again. Lees works it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Slower through the air, around off. Lees defends it towards the off side and takes a single.
Root advances down the track and Keshav Maharaj drags his length back, on middle. Root ends up padding it away.
On a length, on off. Lees pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, around off. Lees defends it towards the off side and looks for a single but is sent back by his partner.
Tad shorter in length, around off. Lees defends it onto the turf.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Lees makes a careful leave.
Lands on a good length again, bit wider outside off and Lees leaves it alone.
Fuller length, on the stumps. Alex Lees plays it towards the point region.
Tossed up on middle. Root paddles it towards the fine leg region for a single.
Bowls it fuller on middle. Lees works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy delivery, on off. Root leans forward and blocks it out.
Root brings out a reverse-sweep now! This is fuller on off. Root kneels and reverse-sweeps it fine through the third man region. They take three. Good running.
Beaten! Pushes it quicker and it is around off. Lees tries to drive it away but gets beaten.
Fuller length, attacking the stumps. Alex Lees drives it towards the cover region.

OUT! CAUGHT! Joe Root departs! A rare twin failure for the former English skipper. This is a big, big wicket for South Africa! Lungi Ngidi is elated and so are other South African players. South Africa are right on top here. This is a fullish delivery, outside off. Root goes with hard hands for a drive and ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball goes straight into the hands of Aiden Markram at second slip and England lose their most dependable batter.
Howout: c Aiden Markram b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary: Ohh...lovely bowling! Ngidi lands it on a length, around off. The ball nips back in sharply and goes just past the off pole as Jonny Bairstow leaves it.
Bowls a yorker, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Serves a length delivery, on off. Jonny Bairstow defends it back to the bowler.
Pulls his length back a bit, outside off at 142 kph. Jonny Bairstow looks to punch it away but does not get any timing in that shot.
Short ball, rises off the pitch. Jonny Bairstow manages to keep it down to the turf.
Tad shorter angling into middle. Lees goes back and punches it to long on for a single.
Tossed up, around leg. Jonny Bairstow works it towards square leg and gets off the mark.
Turning into middle and Lees works it towards mid-wicket with the turn.
Tossed up, on off. Lees drives it to covers.
Bowls it tad shorter and gets good turn. The ball drifts on the pads and Lees works it just past the short fine leg fielder for a single.
Fuller length, on the middle and leg stump. Jonny Bairstow works it towards short leg. The fielder there is quick to react as he stops it and throws it back to the keeper.
Anrich Nortje begins with a length ball, darting it on the thigh pad, at 140 clicks. Alex Lees tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, outside off, nipping in a tad. Jonny Bairstow taps it off the back foot towards cover for a single.
A good-length delivery now, outside off, at 143 kph. Alex Lees leans forward and blocks it towards point.
Angling in, shorter ball, around middle and leg. Alex Lees works it away through mid-wicket for a brace.
Outside off, on a length, at 145 clicks. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Short of good length. That ball didn't bounce as much as Lees expected it to be as he misses his pull shot. Gets hit just around the box.
Tosses this one up, serves it very full, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards mid off.
Another loopy ball, full and around off. Jonny Bairstow leans forward and blocks it out.
Floats this one up, delivers it very full this time, around middle. Jonny Bairstow keeps it out.
Flighted ball, full and around middle and off. Jonny Bairstow prods forward and blocks it out watchfully.

Tosses this one up, bowls it around the off pole, full in length. Jonny Bairstow presses forward and looks to block this but the ball goes off the outside edge away from the first slip fielder. A single taken.
Fuller length, on middle. Alex Lees works it towards the mid-wicket region.

Anrich Nortje bowls it short, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pulls it in the vacant deep mid-wicket region. Kagiso Rabada runs in from deep square leg to cut that one off. He keeps the ball away from the ropes, but the batters run four runs.
On a length now, around middle and off. Jonny Bairstow closes the face of his bat and tucks it towards fine leg. Two taken.
Shorter ball, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow looks to pull this one but he misses and gets hit on his body.
FOUR! Top shot! Short and width on offer this time. Jonny Bairstow rocks back and punches it off the back foot through cover-point for a boundary.
Swing and a miss! A fuller one, outside off. Jonny Bairstow leans to drive this one but he misses.
Good length, on the middle stump line. Jonny Bairstow plays it with straight bat towards the bowler.
Tosses it up, fuller one, around off. Alex Lees prods forward to drive this but the ball goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid on. A single taken.
Loopy ball, full and around off. Jonny Bairstow lunges forward and defends it out.
Tad quicker, around middle, full in length. Jonny Bairstow dances down the pitch and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Spinning in, a fuller ball, around middle. Alex Lees looks to reverse-sweep this one, but the misses. The ball hits his back and goes towards the leg slip fielder.
Pitches it up again, around off, tossed up delivery. Alex Lees pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller length. Alex Lees dances down the pitch and hits it straight in the hands of Keshav Maharaj along the ground.
FOUR! Cut away! A length ball, little bit of width there outside off. Jonny Bairstow rocks back and slashes it past point for a boundary.
Beaten! Lovely ball! Slightly shorter this time, shaping away. Jonny Bairstow looks to push this one away but he gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Anrich Nortje is elated! He knows it's a massive wicket. Anrich Nortje has got Jonny Bairstow for the second time in the match. A good-length delivery, nipping away, around the fourth stump line. Jonny Bairstow sticks his bat out to block this one but the ball goes off the outside edge towards the keeper. Kyle Verreynne pouches it safely. England are in a spot of bother now.
Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Anrich Nortje

Commentary: Anrich Nortje goes 'round the wicket now, serves a length ball, angling in, around middle and leg. Ben Stokes misses his flick and gets hit on his thigh pad.
Wow! Lovely ball! A yorker-length ball, outside off, at 152 clicks! Ben Stokes fails to dig this one out.
Short ball, around off. Ben Stokes plays it very comfortably towards the point region.
Spinning in, shorter ball, around off. Alex Lees stays in his crease and pushes it towards cover for a single.
A fuller ball, turning in, around middle. Ben Stokes looks to reverse-sweep this but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad.
Shorter ball this time, around middle. Ben Stokes pushes it off the back foot towards mid on.
Tosses it up, full, around middle. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee and reverse-sweeps it towards sweeper cover for a single.
Loopy ball, full, spinning in, around middle. Alex Lees blocks it out towards the leg side.
On off and turning in. Lees sweeps and sweeps it well towards the deep backward square leg region. The ball does not travel all the way towards the ropes as the fielder cuts it off. Three taken.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
A good-length delivery, outside off, swinging away. Alex Lees is happy to let that go.
Anrich Nortje drops it short, down the leg side. Alex Lees ducks underneath it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Anrich Nortje has done it once again! Two wickets in two overs for him. South Africa are all over England at the moment. Another peach of a delivery. A length ball, this one land around off and nips away just a tad. Alex Lees stays in his crease and looks to defend this one but gets an outside edge towards the keeper. Kyle Verreynne makes no mistake there. Anrich Nortje has his second wicket and with that England have lost half their side.
Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Anrich Nortje

Commentary: Anrich Nortje comes over the wicket and serves it down the leg side, fuller one. Ben Foakes leaves it alone.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Another one bites the dust. Anrich Nortje is breathing fire at the moment! England are falling apart at Lord's! Anrich Nortje serves a length ball, width on offer this time, shaping away. Ben Foakes rocks back and looks to slash this one away. But he only manages to get an outside edge back to the keeper. Kyle Verreynne once again takes an easy catch. England are 6 down!
Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Anrich Nortje

Commentary: FOUR! Good shot! A shorter ball, spinning in, around middle and off. Ben Stokes uses the depth of his crease and punches it through cover for a boundary.
Tosses this one up, full, around middle and off. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee and reverse-sweeps towards point for a single.

A fuller one, spinning in, around middle. Stuart Broad gets down on his knee and looks to scoop this one. But he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad. A huge appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no. Dean Elgar opts for a review. UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracking shows it clipping the stumps but it's the umpire's call. A good review from South Africa, but the on-field decision stands.
Tosses this one up, full and around off. Stuart Broad blocks it out towards cover.
Swing and a miss! Loopy ball, outside off, fuller one. Stuart Broad looks to sweeps this one but he misses.
Fuller length, darted on the pads. Stuart Broad defends it comfortably.
Back of a length, on middle at 151 kph. Stokes works it towards short fine leg.
A length ball, around middle. Ben Stokes pushes it past mid on for a brace.
Play and a miss! A length ball, swinging back in, outside off. Ben Stokes stays in his crease and looks to cut this one away but he misses.
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes dabs it towards the point region. A single taken.
Shorter ball, around the off pole. Stuart Broad blocks it out towards point.
EDGE! Back-of-a-length delivery, around off. Broad pushes at it away from his body but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes in the air but falls just short of the diving gully fielder.

Leg bye! A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire says no! A fuller ball from 'round the wicket, around off. Ben Stokes looks to sweep this one, but he misses and gets hit on his back pad. South Africa though go up for the review. No bat involved there. The Ball Tracking indicates that it was missing the wickets and the impact was the umpires call as well. Not out it is! There was a throw at the non-striker's end, but well away from the stumps. They cross and get a run as well.
Tosses it up, full, around off. Stuart Broad blocks it out with the inner half of his bat.
Fuller one, around middle and off. Stuart Broad blocks it out.
Turning back in, fuller ball, around middle. Stuart Broad stretches forward to sweep this one but he misses and gets hit on his pad.
This time he connects the sweep! A fuller one, spinning in, around middle. Stuart Broad sweeps it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Good length, outside off. Stuart Broad just plays it towards the point region for a single.
FOUR! Probably this is the only way Broad is going to play against the pacers. It is shorter in length, around off. Broad makes room and cuts it over point for a boundary.
FOUR! Two boundaries in a row now! Nortje bowls it short on middle. Broad backs away and slaps it towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Broad backs away and has a wild swing at it but misses.
On the shorter side again, angling into the body. Broad blocks it away awkwardly.
SIX! Broad with a maximum now! Stuart Broad backs away again and Nortje follows him. He bowls it short and Broad hooks it over deep square leg for a maximum.

In the air..but safe! Broad again shows his stumps and the bowler follows him again, on leg. Broad looks to heave it towards the leg side. However, he gets a huge top edge and the ball goes in the air towards cover-point. Rabada running across to his left dives to catch it but the ball falls away from him. Two taken.
On a length and outside off. Stokes tries to cut it but misses.
On a length and outside off. Stokes skips down the track and looks to go inside out but misses.
A bouncer on middle. Stokes backs away but ends up only blocking it.
Back of a length, on leg. Stokes backing away again tries to clip it. He misses and a leg bye is taken as the ball rolls towards the leg side.
On a length and outside off. Broad throws his bat at it but misses.

EDGED AND FOUR! A fuller one from Marco Jansen, outside off, shaping away. Stuart Broad swings his bat at it and manages to get a thick outside edge. The ball flies over the leaping second slip fielder towards third man for a boundary.

FOUR! Another tough chance goes down! A fuller delivery on off. Stokes hits it hard and straight to Nortje. He gets a good hand to it. However, this catches are always tough on the follow through and the ball deflects off his hand towards the long on fence for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Stokes dabs it towards backward point for a single.
A fullish delivery, around off. Broad backs away and swings hard but misses.
Broad contiunes to throw his bat at everything. Broad makes room and Nortje bowls a full delivery, around leg. Broad misses his slog and the ball goes just past the leg stump.
FOUR! Broad is really enjoying himself here. A full delivery on off. Broad drills it towards the long off fence for a boundary.
Fuller length, outside off. Stuart Broad cuts it towards point but a good stop by Kagiso Rabada keeps it down to a single.
Goes fuller on leg. Broad skips down the track and works it to deep square leg for a single.
A full delivery on leg. Stokes looks to clip it away but misses. The ball goes off his pads towards the leg side. A leg bye taken.

FOUR! Runs are flowing for England here! Jansen bangs it short, on middle. It is a very well-directed short delivery and Broad looks to sway away from the line of the ball. He though keeps his angled bat near the shoulder and the ball kisses the blade to go over the keeper for a boundary.
A full delivery and down the leg sidde. Broad leaves it. Kyle Verreynne dives to his right and half-stops it. A  bye taken. 50 runs partnership comes up.
Full and on the pads. Stokes works it to fine leg for a single.
Good length, down leg. Stuart Broad makes room and looks to go big again, but he fails to get any connection on that.
NO BALL! Back of a length, around off. Stokes guides it to third man for a single. Rabada oversteps here.
Back of a length, on off. Broad heaves it and does not time it properly. However, he ends up getting enough blade to take it over mid on and comes back for the second run.

OUT! CAUGHT! Kagiso Rabada outfoxes Stuart Broad with a slower delivery and breaks this counter-attacking partnership between Broad and Stokes. This was bound to happen sooner rather than later, Broad was going for everything and Rabada is too good a bowler to let him do that regularly. Back of a length, on off. It is a slower delivery and Broad ends up playing it early. He gets the toe-end of his blade as he looks to loft it away and hits it straight to Dean Elgar at mid off. The skipper takes an easy catch and England are seven down now.
Howout: c Dean Elgar b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: A fullish delivery, outside off. Potts throws his bat at it but misses.
On a length, on middle. Potts works it past square leg for a single.
Tad shorter on middle again. Stokes clips it to square leg for a single.
Good length, attacking the stumps. Matthew Potts plays it towards the mid-wicket region.
On a length, on off. Stokes blocks it out.
Goes fuller on middle. Stokes works it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Lands it on a length, around leg. Stokes looks to clip it but misses.
A fullish delivery on middle. Stokes drives it to long on for a single.
Back of a length, around leg. Potts gets across and looks to work it towards the leg side but misses.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Marco Jansen gets his first wicket of this innings and South Africa inch closer to a historic win here at Lord's! This is full and straight on middle. It shapes back in nicely and Potts goes for a big hit down the ground. He misses and the ball shatters the stumps. Jansen is elated and England sink further.
Howout: b Marco Jansen

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Here is the final nail in the coffin! Ben Stokes departs! Rabada bowls it full on middle. Stokes heaves it aerially but does not get enough power behind his shot to clear the fence. it goes flat and towards the deep mid-wicket region where Keshav Maharaj runs to his left and dives to take a good low catch. South Africa are just one wicket away now!
Howout: c Keshav Maharaj b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: Beats him first up! Lands it on a good length, around off. It is angled across and the ball zips past the outside edge of Jimmy's blade as he looks to defend.
On a length and down the leg side. James Anderson looks to clip it away but misses.
NO BALL! Rabada oversteps here! Back of a length, around off. James Anderson defends it towards the off side and takes a single. There is a big roar from the crowd.
Back of a length, around off. Leach guides it towwards backward point. Anrich Nortje moves sharply to his right and stops it with a dive.
NO BALL! Back of a length, on off. Leach dabs it towards point. Another no ball from Rabada.
On a length, on off. Leach gets the inside edge onto his pads as he looks to defend it.
Good length, outside off. Jack Leach pushes it towards point fielder.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. James Anderson tries to drive it away but misses.
Another play and a miss! On a good length and outside off. James Anderson drives away from his body but misses.
Good late swing for Jansen! This is on a fullish length, on off. James Anderson looks to drive it away but the ball swings away and beats the outside edge of Jimmy's blade.

OUT! BOWLED! That's it! South Africa win! What a performance this has been, a true team effort. They stayed true to their strengths playing old-fashioned cricket with great grit and determination and delivered a solid performance in the end. Coming to the ball - This is very full and swings away late from middle. James Anderson skips down the track and backs away a bit too much. He tried to dig it out but is too late as the ball goes onto shatter the stumps. Marco Jansen is elated and so are other players, they truly deserve this win. South Africa win by an innings and 12 runs!
Howout: b Marco Jansen
